messages.content: You arise from your slumber in your EVIL apartment complex. It is a weekday, meaning you are expected to show up to the zoo. You may show up on time, giving you more time to prepare, yet also you may show up slightly late to torment them. Decisions, decisions…

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl takes in the scenery of her apartment and begins a small maniacal chuckle to herself. "Those fools that allow me to live here don't even realize what they've done, do they? It's only a matter of time before I, Voreverl Leocot, can finally reveal the machinations I've been brewing here. Soon I'll have all the minions I need to enact my scheme... Haah, but for now, I, Voreverl Leocot, must attend to the first step of this master scheme." Voreverl gets up from bed and checks her apartment for cereal

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: Voreverl has some cereal stored in her apartment.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Good... Good... With this level of proper supply stocking, running an evil organization from the shadows will be little more than a single step up the evil staircase of doom." Voreverl pours herself a bowl of Trix, her favorite cereal, due to the kids who cruelly torture the rabbit being a strong inspiration for her as a child. After finishing, she prepares herself for work and heads out as soon as she can, as it's important to maintain appearances so her betrayals can sting harder

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
At the front gate, Voreverl encounters her boss.
“…You’re five minutes late. Whatever. Eric is over by the flamingos, see if he needs help. I’ll bug you when I need something.”
She’s preoccupied with her phone at the moment.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Heh, sorry about my tardiness, evil simply runs in a different time zone, to stay ahead of any who get in our way." Voreverl heads over to the flamingos, spending her time on the way to them wondering what the best way to win over their loyalty would be.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Hi Voreverl! Hi.” Eric is dressed entirely in pink, lugging around a bucket of shrimp.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Greetings, Eric. Heheheh, I see you've prepared an outfit today that will truly make anyone who looks upon it despair, quite the genius tactic for a betrayal... Although I'm sad I didn't think of it first, this challenge will only serve to make my future schemes that much stronger."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Haha, yeah.” Eric nods over enthusiastically, as if to put his all into conveying that he really understands what you’re saying.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Well then, the 'boss' wished for me to check if you needed my assistance, which I'll be happy to provide. After all, I'm still a loyal member of this zoo's staff, and clearly always will be." The edges of Voreverl's mouth unconsciously form a smirk as she says the last part of her statement.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: :smirkhuman:

author.name: legoskelton
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\7324d6b2e5e7b2d85c445c799b852d80-F5E1E.png

messages.content:
“Well, I appreciate any help! But…” He looks over your outfit. “Well, okay, this isn’t strictly a thing I was TOLD to do, but I think it’s good for these guys development if they’re able to view the source of their food as one of their own, so…” he gestures to his outfit.

“I like animals.” He smiles and gives a thumbs up. “Uh, it looks like this won’t be enough, some of these guys haven’t even gotten any yet. Could you grab another bucket from the back room?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
"One of their own..." Voreverl is shocked, her mind racing, was that the missing ingredient that her concoction of schemes needed all this time? To allow her minions to view her as one of them? No, no, that can't be it, can it? How can you maintain a sense of authority then... She'll have to think about this carefully.

"Oh, uh!" Voreverl snaps out of her train of thought "Right, thanks for the advice, I'll keep it in mind. One bucket of disposable sea minions coming up." Voreverl heads to the backroom to look for a shrimp bucket.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

author.name: scipe

messages.content: You find the bucket, but receive a call via CELLULAR PHONE just as you do.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "This better be important, I can't allow myself to be distracted from a job as crucial as this. If I don't win over these animals quick enough, the government is sure to catch onto me, even those fools have their limits. One arrest is enough for a villain origin story, I don't need another." Voreverl answers the call.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "Hello, you've reached the aspiring evil mastermind Voreverl Leocot, what insignificant pawn am I speaking to?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: You hear a deep sigh on the other end of the line. “It’s your father, Jane. …Are you still in Italy?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl's voice gets caught in her throat for a moment as she hears this, and pauses for a few seconds before responding "...G- Gweheheh! So you've been tracking my movements, have you, father? Indeed, Italy is the center of all my current schemes. I've wormed my way into organizations the power of which you wouldn't even be able to dream of! I'm really quite busy, due to my success, so what is it that you want?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: There is a substantial pause before you receive a reply. “…Okay. Your mother will be in the area soon. I’m not sure if she intends to visit you or not, but I guess I should let you know ahead of time. I don’t support this… ‘lifestyle’, but…” He trails off.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl does an exaggerated shrugging pose for no one in particular "I wouldn't expect someone like you to get it, no, it's better that you don't. A mastermind is nothing without a society to overturn, after all. But, uh, thanks for letting me know, I suppose. I'm sure mother will be utterly *delighted* to see where I've ended up."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Yeah, good, okay. Just… keep your head up. You’re a Leiblich, whether we can see eye to eye or not. Don’t let yourself become someone else’s pawn.” He hangs up without letting you respond to this.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl's hand tightens around her phone "...Me? A pawn? Hah! Who does he think I am!? And what's with that 'Jane' and 'Leiblich' crap!? Asshole knows that's not my name! Ugh, whatever, soon he won't be able to go anywhere without seeing my real name covering the news! First this zoo, then the world, and he'll see!" Voreverl angrily grabs the bucket and heads back to Eric, grumbling to herself.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: Eric waves. “Thanks!” He takes the bucket.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Well, I'm glad *someone* appreciates my efforts. All things considered, there's certainly worse minions I could've gotten than you. Perhaps I can put off my planned betrayal for a few more days than I had it scheduled. I need the time to figure out how to steal the beanie anyway."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: Eric clutches his hat possessively.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl chuckles to herself for a moment, before changing to a more serious expression and shifting her gaze "...Hey, Eric. Do you have a family?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: Eric tenses up.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “Well… everyone does. But I guess I’m as close as you can get to not having one. We aren’t on speaking terms. I have too much family, one might say.” He lightens up, returning to lovable old Eric Zeety. “Any reason you ask?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I- Uh, well, I was just..." Voreverl balls her hands into fists, digging her nails into her hand "I was wondering who I'd hold for ransom if you turned against me! That's it, yeah! What a shame that you're not too close to them, guess there goes that evil scheme!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: Eric laughs. “That’s Voreverl, alright. Literally never stops with the fantastic jokes.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "It's not a joke! Ugh, maybe I was wrong about your usefulness as a minion. Can't even recognize a genuine evil genius right in front of you. I can only hope there's not more people like you out there, the thought of my first official announcement of my evil intentions on a global scale being met with laughter..." Voreverl shivers

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Personally, I think the best jokes are those that contain elements of sincerity.” Eric strokes his chin thoughtfully.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Well if you have such deep thoughts on comedy, I'm sure you'll enjoy your role as a court jester in my evil empire. Actually, are court jesters even still a thing? The internet might've phased them out. Maybe my evil empire can have, like, an official TikTok or something. Yes, yes, win the public over using their own means of entertainment, make them slaves to our comedy. I'll have to look into this."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Yeah.” Eric exits the flamingo enclosure into the publicly accessible walkways.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl continues mumbling about her schemes as she moves on to do whatever else is in her job description.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: Does anything else occur at Voreverl or is it an uneventful day at the zoo

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: Very strange, but you are approached by a young woman and roll insight

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: Sure. Anyway,

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
She walks up to you. "...That would be it, then. Right among the filthy animals where you belong."

Eric is nearby. "Hey, what's uh, going on?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl is taken off guard for a moment "Huh? Ah, sorry, I was deep in thought on how to win these animals over, trying to build up some minions for my empire, you see. Good to hear that someone else agrees that this is the ideal spot for building up my followers! Animals truly are the easiest to manipulate."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
Eric smiles. "You really do have a way with words, wow."

The woman twitches, then takes a deep breath. "I'm a patient, mature person. I'll hold back from giving you what you deserve if you stop making the act of speaking with you feel like pulling teeth."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Pulling teeth..." Voreverl contemplates this image for a moment "Heheheh, so my machinations are that effective, then? The betrayal of losing one's pearly whites, a mouth unable to chew on its prey. Indeed, an apt comparison for what all civilians will feel after my conquest! You really understand what this is all about."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
She pauses, and fiddles with something you can roll perception for. "You don't even know, do you? Of course. Can't be bothered to think of anyone but yourself."

Eric is uncomfortable.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: ((14 for perception)) "Heh, that's an odd thing to say. I know everything that I need to, and don't bother with anything that won't progress my goals. Other people are just there to fuel my evil conquest or get in its way. So then, you might want to stop acting so superior if you want anything resembling a respectable position in the world once it's under my rules. Pfft, just kidding, I could never stick to such a deal."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
"Hey, Voreverl's a little different from other people, but just because she's all evil doesn't mean she's a bad guy!" Eric speaks out defensively.

Voreverl is perceptive enough to note that the girl has put on brass knuckles. "Try me, Jane. Go ahead. What else do you have to say?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl takes a step back "Ah, hey, uh, whoa there, hold on. I don't think you understand who you're challenging, there's no way that someone as simpleminded as- Wait, Jane? Do I know you from somewhere?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
Voreverl gets punched in the face. In the real world, there are no initiative rolls.

The girl flinches from the impact and asks you something about some person, but you can't make out the name. Eric runs up to her angrily and grabs her by the collar.

You lose consciousness.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: ((Is there like, a floor, or,))

messages.content: Voreverl can't perceive a floor, but is standing on something or other, not just in freefall.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl looks around frantically "What the!? Kidnapped twice in one day!? Or... Wait, is this the other world that planner guy talked about?? I was expecting something more conquerable... But if this is all it is then... What a fantastic betrayal! I'll have to write down the idea to trap someone in a void when I get home, I'm sure Eric would be real surprised by it! ...Though first I have to get out, I guess." Voreverl tries walking around to see if she can stumble upon anything other than just pure black.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: There's a whole lot of not anything.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Ugh... Okay, the evil scheme's effective, I get it, you're good at kidnappings. Does it really need to be drawn out. A good villain understands the importance of pacing! Maybe one of my minions can help, hopefully they weren't foolish enough to fall into the same trap as me... Which I purposefully fell into! To check if it was safe for them! Which if it wasn't I would let them fall into it anyway!" Voreverl yells this clarification to the sky that does not exist and then checks if she has the PDA on her.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: The PDA is there.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: She checks the earth-gc and is about to type a message asking where the others are, but hesitates upon seeing the initials for the messages from the others. She quickly puts the PDA away, she can handle this without the group chat. Voreverl continues walking and begins yelling out the names of her minions (Klaud, Viotto, Voreverl Jr.), hoping for a response.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "I don't recall ever facing a foe quite like that one, no. But conflict does come with the turf. You should be decently equipped for it." They are walking now it is a desert. Wress offers you a canteen.

author.name: scipe

Voreverl looks around for Horatius while fantasizing about evil schemes.

author.name: natyobb

messages.content: "Can't exactly say I understand why someone would build a city here of all places, but even if they don't have the intelligence needed to realize they should move to a better climate, I suppose they could still be useful. So then, minion, what's our first order of business?"

messages.content: "We need to secure the support of the person in charge of this barren expanse. Elithabeza Hifele. She should be working somewhere in the middle of this town."

messages.content: "Diplomacy, huh? Well then, I assume we have a plan ready to coerce her? Kidnapping her family? Threatening to leak her nudes online? Ooh, we could just skip the discussion and brainwash her! So many options as a villain! It's really the most liberating profession."

Voreverl closes her eyes and contemplates for a moment "Yes, yes, I suppose it would still be an intimidating show of power to bend a leader to our will with our mere presence alone! What's a better demonstration of the fear we induce than winning without even trying! Great idea, minion!"

"...State your business." A man seated at a desk past the entrance says this. I am going to give you an opportunity to speak over and before Wress.

"We..." He sighs. "We do want to speak with the chieftain, yes. Just me and h-her." He gestures to the others to stay behind. Furn does not leave.

The man gives the dwayne johnson eyebrow raise. "And your name?"

"W..." Wress pauses. "Nathan Strider."

"I'll pass this along." He leaves your group. Wress stands there idly.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

This happens. They reach a room that could be described as an office, with a woman in it.

"...*You*." Her.

"Hey, okay, look, let me talk first, okay, please?" Wress (addressed to her).

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Gweheheh, trying to get the first word in. A wise tactic, underling. I certainly have trained you well in the art of discussion." Voreverl crosses her arms and and gives a look of pride at Wress, before turning to smugly grin at the woman.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
"...Who the hell is that." The woman turns to you.

"Oh, well, I mean, you must know that I work with a variety of people..."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl sarcastically points to herself, as if asking who the woman is referring to "Oh? You mean me? Are you telling me that you aren't aware of the grand evil mastermind, who will one day rule this world!? I am Voreverl Leocot! Evil incarnate! The plague upon society! Burn this face into your... Uh..." Voreverl looks around nervously for a moment "I... Nevermind... W-Wre... Nathan! You had something you wanted to say, right? Go ahead and... lead the... yeah. Sorry, I just can't conduct evil in this form the same way I usually do."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
"Mhm." The woman looks unamused. "A serious political movement, to be sure." 

"That's! No, she's just... she doesn't trust you, still. It's an informational warfare tactic. Look, this is the real deal!" He looks around to check that A Man has left. "I have plenty of allies already, some of whom were already working with dad. Voreverl here has interplanar knowledge! Horatius isn't here, but they're really cool, I'm sure that I could make this point much better with them. Beza..."

"Don't call me that. And what is 'Horatius'? Are you giving things names just to sound cool?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
"No, that's the guys name."

"Why are you calling one guy 'they'?"

"What? I don't know. You know the Western advisor? It's like that, I think."

"That bitch Arrive? This is ridiculous. I'm going to send your ass to jail and you'll have nobody to blame but yourself."

"No you aren't. Unless you want to be stuck in this dead end shithole for the rest of your life."

"I hope you still appreciate that I have a *real* job."

"Yeah, one that you're clearly not doing very well."

This continues to happen.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl listens to this silently for a bit, biting her lip and balling her hands into fists, before suddenly yelling out "Ugh! Shut the hell up! What is wrong with you two!? I came here to intimidate her into submitting to our empire, and you- you- what even is this!? This isn't even the usual boring political discussion, this is just torture! Listen, I don't give a shit about your 'real job' or any formal procedures here! We're the evil villains, you have what we want, so give it to us already! Just get it over with!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
She laughs. "See, this one, at least, she knows how to get to the point. Sometimes blindly charging ahead for what you want works better than formulating a plan for so long you don't do anything."

Wress pouts.

She looks towards Voreverl. "Empire, eh? You want to take power for yourself, girl?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl looks very proud of herself after being praised "Well, that's one way to phrase it. In the world I come from, I've already toppled society, so simply taking power here doesn't particularly interest me. Running a society sounds so *boring*, all I care about is knocking over what currently stands! The greatest villains don't passively sit upon a throne like those cowardly politicians! No, we destroy! We crumble the foundation of government! That's what I wish for! That is evil!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: She stares at you. "*You* toppled society? And they just had to... sit there and suck it up?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Uh... Y-yeah! That's right! I sent those fools back to the stone age! No more governments! No more religion! No more corporations! No more busy work days! Gweheheh, really they should be thanking me. Every good villain is in the right, and I'm no exception, that's what makes me evil!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: She :livesongpc:, but then smiles. Not a devious smirk or mocking grin. The kind people make when they're happy. "Every day, the fates flip a coin. And if it lands one way, people tell me I don't belong here, while for the other way people tell me I'm setting a terrible example, making my sort look bad. I don't want to break ground, I want to do my fucking job! Less than perfect?! I'm doing my best!" She yells at no one. "Fine, Wress. If you've grown up enough to be willing to let this lady near you, I'll take my chances with you. I hope her methods can lead to your results. And that you turn a blind eye to cousin dearest when you think about being a hardass about procedure."

messages.content: Voreverl takes a moment to process what just happened, and then jumps up and fist pumps in the air "Yes! Now that's what I'm talking about! I-I didn't think it would... Heh, I knew my sheer presence would convince her, that's what we call a good establishment of villainy! And to you," Voreverl begins applauding "Great speech, really! To hell with expectations! To hell with assumptions! We just gotta be who we are! When you fake it, that's when evil can't stand up to good! Don't worry, I'll carry this minion to victory if it's the last act of evil I do!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Oh- Uh, sure, big guy! That lady just lit a fire under me, can't let it be put out by listening to the two of them drone on about details."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "I would like to apologize for my behavior earlier. You are you, regardless of how it happened, and your attitude towards the incident doesn't change that it clearly was not your initial doing." He kneels one leg on the ground. "I will serve your aims while this body still moves, madam."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl drops her prideful attitude for a moment, and takes a step back, straining out some words "You... Right, well... D-Don't worry about... I shouldn't have..." Voreverl runs over to the nearest wall and slams her head into it, not hard enough to knock her out or anything, just enough to hurt, and turns back to Furn with a grin "...Gweheheh... That's what I thought, minion! You have my thanks for realizing the error of your ways! Now get up! We can't have someone in my army appearing weak!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
Furn nods, and gets up. It looks like they're about done this conversation.

Wress returns. "Okay. One down, four to go. Let's head out before we draw trouble her way."

messages.content: "Good idea, minion! The last thing I want is to be stuck in some random city in the middle of a wasteland. Every evil mastermind needs a beautiful backdrop for their villainous poses, after all."

messages.content:
"When I bring destruction to mind, there is an ever-present symbology, is there not? Fire... to burn, to reduce to ashes. That is, as a counterpart, the expression of a broken external cycle. Fire reverts you to the past... to a time when humans lacked art, culture, animal domestication, everything important to us! Fighting back against that... preparing for that... it is genuinely the most human thing imaginable! Please, understand what I am saying!"
A guy is screaming this in public. Also it's Viotto you recognize his voice even if you can't quite see him.

Voreverl turns towards Wress "And what are *you* so concerned about? So they know the twist villain a little early, big deal."

messages.content: "I just... I heard you back there, that whole speech. I know what someone talking about their ideals sounds like, and I know what someone trying to fit with an image they're attempting to craft sounds like." He narrows his eyes. "You're not a sadist. So what the hell are you?"

Just like all the best villains, I'm pure evil and I fight for nothing but evil! Don't try to psychoanalyze me, because you're clearly failing at it, hard!"

messages.content:
*Voreverl Leocot - *
That is your name, yeah? It's what stuff on your person seems to indicate and what other people have attested to. It doesn't feel like a real name to me? But I guess I know nothing about what is normal here.
I'm Bernard Zie. Hopefully you've learned that much (?). I'm from a kingdom called Arctica, whereas you're in the nation "Italy".
I was in your body. I woke up in a room designed for treating the ill that turns out to be affiliated with a place that keeps animals imprisoned. I freaked out a little, being in such inexplicable circumstances. Eventually, since I didn't know where I lived and neither did Eric, he invited me to stay at his home. I accepted, of course.
I don't know how I'm going to get this message to you. I thought Italy might be some remote island we don't know about, but unless there's a massive effort to mislead me specifically, there seems to be a whole complete spherical world with no Arctica in it. I'm effectively in an entirely different world. I'm going to guess there's probably like two different possibilities.
1. You will awaken back in this body eventually without my action
2. You won't
Ok I mean laying it out like that it seems kind of obvious it has to be one or the other. That was maybe a waste to even write. Also Eric says you can use the tablet things to write text but I don't even want to start with that thing sorry if this is something Italians or Earthans in general arent used to
I guess I'll go over both these possibilities.
In the case of 2, I'm kind of fucked. I'll have to spend a long time researching stuff to even verify the existence of Arctica from here. If this is the case I guess I'll include a followup note explaining what I found and how I got the note to you

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
If it's 1, you'll just find this note on your person, since I plan to keep it on me until I know a certain way to send it to you. And that will also mean this was a waste of time to go over. This stupid bougie pencil doesn't even have an eraser god form over function fucking terrible
I want to get my body back eventually, and to solve the mystery of why this happened at all. And I have a feeling I can't do that without you.
Call me a hopeless romantic, but as distressing as this situation is... I feel like I know you. Literally becoming someone is an unusual empathic experience. You have my body. I have yours. Or maybe even such possessive terms is overly limiting for us now. I'm placing my full trust in you, okay? Please.
Anyway, here's the thing. I'm kind of assuming that it's 1 rather than 2. And making some other assumptions as well. See I do know a little bit about this situation. Maybe a surprising amount, though I guess you might know things I don't. My father (his name ~~is~~ was Ernest) did research that sometimes involved souls and while they can conceptually be transferred in any way you want, in practice a soul is bonded to its vessel and will gravitate back there inevitably. Also I'm assuming you're in my body because that sort of symmetry is common and it being occupied would be one thing preventing me from snapping back immediately. So unless someone's expending a lot of energy I think we'll have to end up back where we started. 
But I don't want that? Or like I don't want that to be it. The other thing my father researched was something relating to "Earth".

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
I'm freaking out a little right now because I just asked Eric if this world at large has a name and he said Earth and I know that word. My father referred to it as a place where people have control over their own lives, where the people in power work to help the people out of it. I always thought he must have meant it metaphorically somehow, using an archaic word for dirt to refer to a grassroots political movement? He said a lot of really weird things. But this is it. Your king isn't even called a king he gets chosen by everyone!!! This is oh my god this is what I've been talking about and Wress kept making fun of me for "reading my dads fanfiction" but its true and its real and its possible!
I don't know what I want now. I'd like to go here? As me. But I also want everyone to know this place exists, so my world can have what you do. The two of us are the only ones with the power to prove that there's an entire world beyond the knowledge of everyone we know. I won't do anything crazy without hearing from you first but we need to do something. Please write some form of acknowledgement back to me

Other Information you might want to know:
The girl who knocked you unconscious was named Violetta Esposito. She's being detained somewhere for aggravated assault. I asked Eric (Zeety) to take me to her but he said it doesn't work that way
I took out the things in your ears and put them in your pocket. It bugs me
Questions for you:
Eric knows common but it seems like everybody else is speaking something else? Like some degenerated Elvish? What's up with that?
[Large portion of crossed out text]
What is "Antarctica"? Sometimes when I ask questions Eric starts to doubt I'm really not you playing some sort of trick so I'd rather not ask him
Do you have any experience with taking care of plants?

Thanks.
- Bern

messages.content:
"Great preparation, you're a valuable asset." Voreverl begins writing out a message in it.

> Read my words carefully, fool. This body belongs to Voreverl Leocot, as does the body I made use of in Arctica. They are under my possession, and will be used to my ends. Right now you are the only one who can protect my bodies when I'm gone, so you remain a useful minion. As long as you follow the chain of command, we will have no issues.
> 
> First of all, this is my address: [Voreverl's address]. Even if your primitive mind has not learned Italian, asking for directions with this should be simple. 
> 
> As for the rest of your letter, let's make this clear: Do not doubt my name again. Do not act like you know me again. And finally, drop your fanboying over the government of my world!!! The people in power are selfish liars. At least evil kings in fiction are openly evil! Evil politicians are so lame in comparison, I can't understand why you want to bring them to Arctica. 
> 
> Since we've established that I'm in charge, here's what's going to happen. In Arctica, you will continue to assist Wress in bringing society to collapse. On Earth, you will take care of the animals in the zoo as Eric and Isidora instruct you to. I am undercover here, as trying to take down Earth's society directly would be foolish. Eventually, we will collapse both governments, and fulfill the title of evil mastermind.
> 
> As your boss, I will fill you in on what you've failed to gather yourself:
> -The language most common in Italy is Italian. Obviously. Since you don't know it, just perform this hand sign 🤌 when you need to express something to someone who only speaks it.
> -Antarctica is a continent on Earth. It's a giant, frozen, boring wasteland with no civilization. Basically, what our end goal for society should be. I doubt it has any relevance to Arctica.
> -I once kept a venus flytrap (The most evil plant), but it died fairly quickly. I'm much better with animals, they're easier to understand than those silent plants.

She rips the page out of the notebook, folds it up and puts it in her pocket. "My apologies for taking up so much time, I had more to write than I expected. That fool must've infected me with his rambling. Ugh, if only he knew how to operate a phone. And what's his problem with earrings? I guess I shouldn't expect one who wears a flower in his hair to have good fashion taste." Voreverl fishes around her pockets for her earrings and puts them back in her ears if they're there. She also hands the notebook and pen back to Eric.

messages.content:
Voreverl calmly enters her apartment and, finally alone after a long day, falls to her knees and begins to hyperventilate. "Wh-what the... What the hell was any of that...!? I-I..." She takes another look at her PDA "That really... All happened... I-I helped... No, I led a terrorist group...!? G-Good, that's... Yeah, I'm... I'm Voreverl Leocot, I mastermind villainous schemes all the time... L-like when I fed the animals the wrong kind of food... Th-this is just like that! This is normal for me, I..." Voreverl slaps herself across the face "I'm rising above this foolish career as a zoo worker! GwehehehAHAHA! Voreverl Leocot finally has minions, she finally has minions, I finally have minions! Once we topple Arctica, I can bring them here! If Viotto and Klaud can appear in Arctica normally, surely a genius like me can bring someone like Fern or Horatius to Earth! That'll show anyone who doubted my power!"

Voreverl finishes hyping herself up and turns her television to whatever's on right now. Preferably something with a good villain to inspire her. She browses social media absentmindedly while watching it and does this until something eventful happens. Evil masterminds need to enjoy their days off.

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "He's... your father means well, really, he just... you..." She shakes her head. "You're my daughter, and I love you, and I'm here because I'm worried. Have you heard of 'The Antarctica Project'?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Antarctica again...?" Voreverl gives a very confused look towards her mother as she processes this "I have to admit that whatever that foolish moniker refers to has slipped under my radar. Do you care to explain rather than just offering shallow concern?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "Again? Am I already too late? If this nonsense has already started, you're in serious danger, uh-Voreverl!" She's freaking out. "Of course you just go ahead and do it, who gives a shit what your *WIFE*--look, whatever you've gone through recently really happened, even getting back to your life here is part of this ridiculous plan! You need to get out of this town and lose whoever they've sent to tail you or it's going to keep happening."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl goes silent for a few moments as her eyes begin darting around, before she closes them and takes a deep breath "...Gw-Gweheh.... Gwehehahah! So *that's* it, huh!? Oh, genius, just utterly brilliant! Of course, Voreverl Leocot couldn't just go conquer a magical world on her own, no, it had to be planned by my family! Well isn't that just great! Can't force me down a career path so you'll use me as a lab rat in some magical scheme, huh!? What, are you trying to guide me to the next objective!? Can't wait to see me have another go at getting my head nearly fucking frozen off!? Ugh, I can't believe I actually thought I was accomplishing something."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
She is taken aback. "Oh, and you're just fine without my advice? Living in a god damn hovel on parole from... ugh! I had nothing to do with this, that project's a psychotic mistake! But if you're so committed to conspiracy theories about me, that's fine! I'll sit there and bear it! That's my role!"

She sighs. "I'm staying at the Hotel Artemide. If you're interested in not being led to your death, come see me there. I'm tired of leading a horse to water, Jane."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl begins pulling at her hair in frustration "...You don't get it! You obviously just don't understand anything! I'm not Jane, I'm not your daughter, and yes, I *have* been fine on my own! I'll believe whatever the hell I want, but frankly, I don't care if you had anything to do with this! I'll find my own way to win, you won't be able to deny Voreverl Leocot once I do! No one will!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "You're just like him, you know." She leaves.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl slams the door to her apartment shut, and then takes out her PDA, staring at it in disgust, before chucking it against the wall at full force "What the hell... What the hell was the point of any of this!? Why can't I just have this one thing! Ugh! Those assholes!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: The PDA hits the wall and then falls to the floor.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I just... I just wanted... Why can't I just live how I want!? What's with these bullshit rules!? So I don't get to decide to go to Arctica!? So I don't get to decide to keep my body!? So I don't get to decide if someone else can run around in it without my permission!? So I don't get to decide if I own the Pope's car!? Fuck, I don't even get to decide my own name!? Ugh!" Voreverl stares at her tossed PDA "That's it, I can't just keep sitting around and waiting for life to bend over backwards, if I'm going to make an evil organization, I have to *make* it!" She picks up the PDA and begins typing into it, assuming it's not broken.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: It works.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl Leocot is still on her PDA. She is angrily grumbling to herself about her mother while typing.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
Voreverl Leocot will now do something else. She begins pacing around the room. "Gweheheh... Soon those foolish parents of mine will see what kind of force of nature they've pitted themselves against. Although, I must admit, I am underperforming a bit in the information department. Perhaps I should not have turned away my mother so quickly, she might have been useful... Ugh, if I visit her now I might have to apologize to get more out of her. I want to have as much information as I can though... Well, if she was being honest and my father is involved, interrogating him is worth a shot."

Voreverl pulls out her phone and attempts to call the number her father used this morning.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: It does eventually get picked up. The voice on the other end of the line is him, sounding a little out of it. "Voreverl, what the hell..."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I've figured out your game, father! I know about The Antarctica Project! So you can stop playing dumb, you know why I'm calling."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "Huh? I'm not some epic arch-rival to you. At least don't subject me to your delusions without me contacting you first."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Gweheheh, please, like I'd consider someone like you worthy of matching up to me! Regardless, you're the one who made the first move, father! Mother told me all about it, so you can't claim I'm the delusional one here!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: There's a pause on the other end of the line. Then laughter. "Hm. That's right, Voreverl. What are you going to do about it? Gonna run away from my project, leave my plans unimpeded?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl is taken aback for a moment "W-wait, you're just... Gweheheh, so my interrogation skills are that advanced, you folded so easily! Like I would ever run away from the challenge of someone beneath me! I don't know what you're planning, but I'll raze Arctica to the ground if I have to to stop whatever it is!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "I'd like to see you try!" He hangs up.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
Voreverl just kind of stands there for a moment before looking at her phone, after a long pause she begins speaking to herself "Wh-what the fuck was that... I-I... So this is... He really is..." She begins to feel a bit dizzy from that conversation and sits down. After taking a minute to collect herself, a smirk rises to her face "...Gweheh... Gweheheh...... GWEHAHAHAHA! Yes, YES! This will serve as the story of my rise! This will be the truth of Voreverl Leocot! My path in life has never been more clear, here it is, an enemy to topple! The pope is a small fry in comparison to this! That buffoon of a father has mistaken himself for a chess master, when he's merely a puppet on strings! My strings! Evil strings! The evil string forming the noose I'll tighten around the neck of society!"

Voreverl slips her PDA and phone back into her pocket and prepares to leave "Mother mentioned that I was being tailed, that is simply unacceptable. Voreverl Leocot is the one who works from the shadows, she does not get worked at from the shadows! If father is being unhelpful, then I will interrogate his lackey." Voreverl exits her apartment and begins walking nowhere in particular, trying to keep an eye out for anyone following her.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: Voreverl is interrupted by a man standing outside her door. “Excuse me, are you…” He checks his phone. “Voreverl Leocot?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Oh- Uh! Gweheh, I see you're well informed. Indeed, I, Voreverl Leocot, am the one you seek. But for what reason have you come to my lair?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Lair?” He clicks his tongue. “Do you live here alone?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Well you're certainly prying for information, without offering any in return. What does it matter to you if I have minions here or not?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: He looks vaguely at the small apartment. “Do you have… an online presence?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Each irritating question you ask, I get closer to sicking my minions onto you. I browse the web, an evil mastermind has to stay up to date, but I don't really have an account for followers of my organization to check. You know, busy with my schemes and all that. I'll get a social media manager at some point."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Though you have a previous criminal record…” He sighs. “Thank your lucky stars this isn’t the United States, I guess.” The man turns to leave.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl grabs his shoulder "Hey! I'm glad to hear you know of my past plots, but did you just come to admire me or is there some reason you're digging this up?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “None of your business, miss.” He pushes you away.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl stares suspiciously at him "Well, if you were working for my father, you'd already know everything you need to, so that can't be it. Could it be that I have two enemies to worry about? Makes sense, I'm just surprised you're coming at me all at the same time, assuming there's no coordination."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Father? The hell are you talking about. We got an anonymous tip about your home. It had zero credibility, but we’re obligated to send *someone* out on all of these, if only to warn people some dumbass kid is trying to SWAT them. I can’t say you’ve made me any *less* suspicious, but I still think this tiny place ain’t worth our while.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Not... Not worth your while!? Do you know who the hell I am!? Whoever that 'dumbass kid' was, they're a lot smarter than you! I'm the lord of evil! I'm the spawn of hell itself! Whatever illegal activity you suspect me of, I'm sure I've done way worse! Don't just dismiss me because of appearances, asshole!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Sure thing, kid.” He again makes to head off.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Ugh! No respect for masterminds these days!" Voreverl allows him to leave and then storms off in a different direction, resuming her plan of trying to notice if she has a tail.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: ((Roll perception))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: The streets of Rome are beautiful. Also no one is following you

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
Voreverl Leocot is of the opinion that Rome would look better if it was all cyberpunk or post-apocalyptic or something.

She lets out a groan "If no one is following me... Who the hell am I supposed to get answers from? Can I just swap back already, at least I had minions there actually *with* me, rather than ignoring my invitation online." She sighs and thinks for a moment before throwing up her hands in frustration "Fine! I'll go! Whatever!" After yelling to herself in the streets of a city, she begins heading towards Hotel Artemide.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: She arrives there. Meryl Leiblich is visible using a computer in the lobby.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl takes a deep breath and walks over to Meryl, before calling out to her "Hello, mother! It is I, your daughter, J-" she cringes "It is I, your daughter, and I am here to make amends!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Oh, um… okay.” She sits there awkwardly.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I would like to formerly apologize for, uh... doing... being, uh... I..." Voreverl puts a hand to her head "Ugh! I just can't! Voreverl Leocot does not apologize! Just tell me what you know so I can leave!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “I don’t know anything more, that’s the problem. I’m going to go speak with the pope. You can come if you want.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl's eyes light up "A-a chance to... A rematch of my mind against his!? Gweheheh, of all the surprises this day has held, this one pleases me the most. Although, I fail to see his relevance."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “I’m still not really used to how broad in scope all of this is… but he’ll know what’s happening, I’m sure of it.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Pfft, like he ever knows what's happening. If he can't even stop me from stealing his car, how exactly is he gonna help us here? I'm all for seeing him, but expecting him to help seems like asking too much of the old bag of bones."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Oh. I didn’t think about that, somehow. I’m sure it’s fine. He doesn’t hold grudges.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Yeah, yeah, I'm sure he's so much greater than the rest of us. I'll squeeze the humanity back into him when I tear down his society."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: Meryl sighs, then start walking.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl follows after her.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: She goes to her car and then if Voreverl also goes in the car she drives the   car

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl makes sure to call shotgun even though they are the only two people getting in the car. Also she gets in it.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: Awesome

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: ((This is the end of Voreverl session I can't simply wing meeting the pope))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: You are in the car.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “Meet any new people around here lately?” Meryl makes a cringe attempt at small talk.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "This country is full of as many fools as any other. I did find a somewhat useful minion at work, though one of the visitors has been trying to interfere with my schemes. Some people just don't know when they're up against more than they can handle."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Mm. Well, it’s good that you’ve found yourself something to do. You must’ve adapted to the language barrier pretty seamlessly.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Gweheheh, of course. A genius mastermind cannot allow communication failure between them and their underlings. All of the best villains in history spoke Italian anyway."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: She frowns. “There’s nothing wrong with being Italian, you know.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl sighs "That was a compliment, mother. Think of all the great Italian villains: Julius Caesar, Benito Mussolini, Diavolo! Sure, the average Italian is nothing special, but it's created some examples to really look up to!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “I don’t think all of those were real names.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I'm allowed to appreciate fictional villains too. It's much easier to learn about and copy their evil schemes if I can see their lives rather than just googling their history."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “No, the devil is real. But he’s not Italian.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Well then, I look forward to conquering his domain after my time ruling the Earth is over. Or rather, *if* my time is ever over. I can probably upload myself into a computer or something, AIs make for fantastic villains."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “AI…” Meryl stares ahead and accelerates. “Mhm. But, just as an abstract goal, to use someone else’s development? Since you very apparently had no passion for CS. A shame! I would’ve been fine with that! I thought medicine would work best, but I’m willing to support my daughter’s ambitions, whatever they may be! Because that’s what a mother does!”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Ugh, why in the world would I waste my time toiling away at some lame science project. That's what underlings do! I need an exciting life, the life of a villain! I'll let those nerds develop the technology and steal it for myself! Besides, no one ever got famous for being a scientist, it's such an inoffensive job. Everyone knows Frankenstein, but no one knows Frankenstein's scientist!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
“Frankenstein *was* the name of the scientist!!” She slams on the brakes. “We’re here.” 
She storms off.

Though your guard attempted to suppress me, they were no match for my skill! Now then, you shall give us the information we seek, or I shall torture it out of you myself!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png
