author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl slowly raises her arms up "Oh, uh... Gweheheh, did I say torture...? Just a, uh, inside joke! Oh man, did I make a wrong turn? No idea how I ended up in the Vatican, really a huge misunderstanding! My bad!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
Meryl groans.

The Pope utters his legendary first words. “…Is that a gun?”

The guard is confused. “Yes, Father.”

“I see. And you are the car thief, yes?” Directed to you.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl looks proud of herself "Well, I'll give you one thing, you've got a better idea of your enemies than most I come across. That was merely one of my numerous schemes, but yes, it's an accurate memory of events."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
“Yes, indeed… but I would know if that same person had instigated a prison break. Your presence here means your sentence has ended. So, then, what crime has she committed to draw your attention?” He stares at the guard.

“W-Well… trespassing.”

“I see. And who told you to respond with lethal force to such an offense? I’m coming on in years, but I’m fairly certain I wouldn’t say such a thing. A man I hold in quite high regard once decried the act of murder.” He lets out a mischievous curl of the lip. The guard backs away sheepishly.

Meryl breathes a sigh of relief.

Pope Francis nods. “Thank you. Now, why are you here?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Sure, I can cut to the chase, as a show of thanks for you foolishly underestimating me with your mercy. Honestly, I have no idea why I'm here! I'm accompanying that woman, who believes you have information that can help us. That seems unlikely to me, but I couldn't pass up the opportunity for a rematch in our ongoing battle of wits."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
Meryl sighs. “Yes. This is my… daughter.”

Pope Francis, head of the Catholic Church, stifles a small laugh. “A curious twist of fate. This is about Antarctica, then?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "...I guess? Though really, I have no idea how any of this connects to that frozen wasteland. Seems like just a case of coincidentally similar names."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Well, it’s no coincidence. The Antarctica Project started in exactly the location you’d expect. And they named the tree that grew from rotten soil accordingly; as the inverse of an inverse.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
“Yes, so I’ve heard.” Meryl sounds impatient. “But what about *now*? What the hell is John doing?”

“Language. And I couldn’t tell you that specifically. I haven’t had any successful contact with John Leiblich for quite some time.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Tsk, tsk, you fools really are lost without a proper evil leader. Let me spell it out: that fool of a father is challenging me! He's finally recognized my talent as a villain, and attempted to trap me in this other world! Why else would he involve his own daughter in this scheme? He knows the danger that I pose to society and is reacting accordingly!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
“…Yes. I don’t understand why, but that man has apparently seen fit to involve you in all of this. It is a safe assumption that he is no longer willing to be even remotely cooperative.”

Meryl looks down at her feet.

“There is an element of madness to John… the kind born of passion. I know it well.” The pope sighs. “We do need to stop whatever this is that’s now being called The Antarctica Project, though.”

“Yes, of course, but how?!” Meryl.

The Pope stares ahead thoughtfully.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Stop it...? Oh, you simpleminded buffoons, you think too small! We don't need to stop it, we need to seize it for ourselves! Or, well, I do, at least. You two can help if you want, not that I need it. All I'm saying is that real victory doesn't come from simply blocking a path, but buying up that path and rubbing it in the face of your enemies!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
“I don’t know… I mean, my first concern is that you make it out of this…” Meryl.

“I admire your commitment to your family, but anything other than the complete annihilation of The Antarctica Project is out of the question. We cannot defeat witchcraft with witchcraft, or save the Earth by taking over the means that will destroy it. I will not concede to the Leiblich family — any member — any more than I would make concessions to the UN.” Papa Frank.

“I guess…” Meryl.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Listen up you fogey, I don't need your permission on this, and saving the Earth is, like, in the negatives on my priority list. I came here for information, not to be lectured on how to approach the situation, to be quite honest, I don't even know if I have gotten *any* information yet! The project started in Antarctica, good for it, but what the hell is it!?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “It is… another world.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Wow! Big revelation there! I've already been to the other world, asshole! And how exactly did another world 'start' in Antarctica? News flash, that's on this world!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “I’m not clear on how or why it was begun where it was. I do have many things going on in my life that aren’t worrying about a specific group of madmen. But that is where the technology creating the false reality was developed. By the den of wolves that go by UNICR.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "...False reality? So, wait, Fainda was right, then? Is the whole thing just some kind of simulation or illusion? I haven't made any progress on conquering a real world!?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Yes. I’m not any kind of technological savant, but Arctica is a fabrication. The fact is merely distorted by theatrics. In fact…” He adjusts his glasses. “Perhaps the most effective counter to The Antarctica Project would be to expose it to the public. Sunlight being the disinfectant, as they say.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
“But I can’t think of a way to do that. Even with my influence, it’s difficult to imagine a way that doesn’t make me sound as if I’ve lost it to all but the most devout.”

“Maybe build up to it gradually?” Meryl.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Okay, hold on, I'm all for you ruining you reputation, but why do you even care? When I thought Arctica was real, there were so many possibilities open to make use of it... but what can even be done with a fake world!? What danger does this even pose anyone!? How is this different from just some advanced video game!?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
“On a personal level, the arrogance in deliberately taking on the role of a God is reprehensible to me.” Meryl nods at this part. “But it’s more than that. The lives of every single human could be endangered by the…” He stops. “Hang on. You’ve *been* to Arctica, yes?”
He signals for Meryl to come closer.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: The question is addressed to Voreverl.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Uh, yeah? I thought I made that clear. Look, I love talking about my escapades as a villain, but I'm getting kind of sick of how long this explanation is taking."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
He and Meryl do some whispering, which you may attempt to eavesdrop on. 

“I apologize for taking up so much of your time. Your goal is to attain the sort of power they have for yourself, and thwart the ambitions of Meryl’s husband, then?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl attempts to listen in on the whispers yeah ((16 for perception which is i assume what you will ask me to roll yup))

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
Yeah.

Pope: “….this girl?”

Meryl: “at least a decade at this… didn’t think it’d last for…”

Pope: “but no…is truly devoid of goals… is she amicable to negotiation?”

Meryl: “hell if I know, it’s…”

The Pope (forma de present) speaks again. “It’s not something you had control over, but if you gained access to Arctica once, it may happen again.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Well, I *was* looking forward to returning to Arctica, but now that I know it's a simulation, that's really put a damper on the whole mood. I struggle to think of what exactly I could gain from stealing my father's work for myself if that's all it's capable of. Maybe it would be better to let him rot alone with his silly science project."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
“That’s not entirely the truth. After all, even if the endgame was nothing but fraud, this group really had the resources to seamlessly kidnap you while you slept, and I believe to do so to some amount of others. Their goals may be foolish, but the power they wield is real.” 

The Pope of the Catholic Church rises from his seat and begins walking over. “I’m offering a *partnership*, Miss Leocot. Our aims are different — very much so — but they match for the near future. I have no interest in what becomes of the means of UNICR or John Leiblich or whatever shadowy conspiracy heads are behind all of this. I just want what they are currently being used for to end.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Gweheheh, I see, so that's it then? The head of the most powerful religious group in the world, groveling at my feet, asking for me to help. Now *this* is what I'm talking about! Very well, you make a good point. Whether Arctica is useful to me or not, toppling this scheme will be a grand first step towards my goals!" Voreverl holds out her hand for a handshake "You've got a deal, Franny! Welcome to my entourage of minions!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
He meets your hand and shakes it. “Welcome to the Earth Defense Force. Or whatever vestiges are left.”

Meryl is resigned to the absurdity of life.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: (( I’m so glad Voreverl has entered this mutually beneficial arrangement. At no point in the future will she betray it. ))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Well, the name could use some work, but it sounds cool enough for now. I'd love to discuss where to start with fighting against this scheme, but before I forget, I'd like to ask a favor. One of the humans foolish enough to be kidnapped alongside me has made contact with me here on Earth. The problem is that she's in Japan right now. Do you think you could, uh, arrange a flight to get her over here? The more minions, the more devious the plot we can cook up, you know?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
Pope Francis thinks it over. “It’s true, the ideal would be for everyone affected to work to sabotage the project. And those with their lives disrupted should already have reason to support us. But what if there’s a mole among them to keep things running smoothly? Why, for all we know, you could be the only one not in on it thanks to the unusual circumstances of your inclusion.”

He shakes his head.

“I don’t think that’s likely, but we can’t be too cautious here. It would draw far too much attention for me to arrange a specific flight in Japan. Is she lacking in means to book a flight herself? Providing her with money discreetly might be possible.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Well, she's certainly not the sharpest tool in the evil shed, her not making a livable wage just makes sense. She gave me her number, so I can ask about her financial situation, I guess. Also, about the mole... there was one participant who already made an attempt on my life. It was a resounding failure, of course, but that does lend credence to the idea of us facing betrayal... Gweheh, I'm almost proud of them."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
“Here is my personal phone number.” The Pope hands you a slip of paper he’s written on. “You can contact me if you want to ask more specific questions. I’ve tried to cover everything I know about The Antarctica Project already, but I can provide other information I may have neglected to mention if you have specific questions. I’ll also see to it that your parole travel restrictions are lifted; that’s something I can easily explain away without drawing suspicion.  And if you’re ever in dire need of last resort transport… I do still have the car, aha.”

The Pope seems to realize something. “Oh, right. You’re a young adult 21st century kid, you probably play the computer games, yes?” He rustles through some drawers before pulling out a steam gift code for the game Undertale. “This isn’t particularly important, but you may have it. I have no use for it.”

“Okay.” Meryl finally speaks up.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "So, uh, what exactly am I supposed to do now? Just wait like a sitting duck for them to kidnap me again, or what? I mean, obviously I can think up a scheme on my own, but did either of you two have anything in mind? I'm raring to get to work on toppling this scheme."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
“What we need more than anything is information. John would have all of it, but he has become consumed by his irrational feelings. There is no active approach I can think of for the near future that is not searching blindly. Just, try to watch your back, I suppose?”

Meryl finally says multiple words at a time. “Hang on. If she’s getting brought there by some technological nonsense, that’s one thing, but I’m not on board with letting someone kidnap my child.” She turns to you. “Voreverl, let’s go home. Please.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl gives a look of disdain towards Meryl "Listen, Mrs. Leiblich, I've played along with your foolish feelings towards me to get this far, but it's clear you've run your course on useful suggestions. I told you before, I'm not your daughter, so you can go ahead and return home on your own. Voreverl Leocot has worlds to conquer." Voreverl turns towards the pope "I'll be in touch." She begins heading out.

Voreverl leaves successfully.

messages.content:
Voreverl Leocot wakes up in a small room, with a metal door and metal hatch on the ground. In this room are Horatius Kyodu, Wress Hifele, and someone you do not recognize. Most of this final person's body is obscured by their armored clothing, which includes strings running across their torso that form a shape that looks like :wyrdwyrd:. The place where their face would be looks like television static.

#horatius-voreverl

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

inlineEmojis.name: wyrdwyrd
inlineEmojis.imageUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\966890007677780048-1693B.png

messages.content: Voreverl Leocot is on the second floor of this building, if we assume the one she started on was the first. Up ahead, :wyrdwyrd: from Wyrd is beating up some more guys. From behind, guys are chasing her.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

inlineEmojis.name: wyrdwyrd
inlineEmojis.imageUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\966890007677780048-1693B.png

messages.content: "Ugh, where the hell even are we!? How were you guys incompetent enough to get trapped here!?" Voreverl Leocot does not have any more actions on her turn if we are still in combat.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: Wyrd again knocks everyone down and runs ahead. Two more guards notice and run up to Voreverl. Two of the ones chasing successfully land a hit, doing a collective 13 damage. Back to Voreverl's turn.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl angrily yells out "Look! I don't know who you guys are, but whatever the previous fool who controlled this body did to piss you off is irrelevant! I didn't even know this place was guarded until I ran into you guys! I've served my time before, I know prison breaks will fail! Just arrest me or something, I'm not fighting back! Destroying society from the inside is *much* more villainous anyway." Voreverl raises her hands to signal surrender, and uses the dodge action just in case. End of turn.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: They seem kind of unsure, but one of them closes in, weapon still in hand. They seem to accept the surrender. Then they fall down and collapse. Then Voreverl also falls down and collapses. ((End session.))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: You wake up in what looks like a prison cell, tied to a chair. Across from you is Furn.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: (( @Natyobb ))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

mentions.name: natyobb
mentions.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: Voreverl's face is filled with amusement at the sight of Furn "So, they really did catch someone like you. Gweheheh, don't worry, Voreverl Leocot does not respect the laws of this prison! Breaking out a criminal like you shall be my next great act of evil to strike fear into the hearts of the masses!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "...Voreverl Leocot." He pauses. "No, that was earlier. The prison break preceded when you awoke, to my understanding. Right now the others are in the middle of some negotiation, or maybe it's a fight at this point."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Oh is that what we were doing here... I guess I can applaud their efforts, they did learn from the best: me. Now that I allowed myself to be captured, we can destroy this prison from the inside out!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "...You can certainly try. I doubt it, though. You're not going anywhere until I'm satisfied."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Pfft, what is that supposed to mean? You follow my instructions, I thought we established this. Or do *you* want to disobey me too? Ugh, minions are getting so full of themselves these days. Maybe you just feel inferior when in the presence of someone as great as I."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "..." Furn stares at you unmovingly.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I was not kept in a cell like this. You may remember that I was not present when you awoke earlier; this is because I was detained into a storage room for confiscated items. I found something there." Furn pulls out what looks like a metal stick.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "There is a contradiction inherent to the situation I am placed in; that I must work to influence you, yet I cannot bring myself to harm the body you inhabit. Bern needs his strength, to be sure. Injuring him would be unthinkable. But using what was presumably designed for a construct like me, it is possible to inflict pain without lasting damage to the body." The stick crackles with electricity. "I am going to ask you some questions. Is this acceptable, Voreverl Leocot?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: ((hey guys welcome back to the antarctica project, the wacky dungeons and dragons campaign where you get transported into a magical isekai world. in this episode voreverl gets waterboarded))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Wh-what the fuck is wrong with all of you!? No, it is not acceptable! Obviously! Ugh, there's so much wrong with what you just said! First of all, if you're going to torture me, don't hold back because of that idiot who used to be in my body! Second, do you know how degrading it is for a mastermind to be shown in a fragile state like this!? I'm above this! Now stop screwing around and untie me!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "There it is again. You want people to hate you; to view you as an antagonist to be beaten, a foe to betray. And yet you are upset when people do not behave in alignment with your wants. One of these is a lie."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "...That can wait. First, you mentioned this world being 'fake'. What did you mean by this?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "It can wait? It can wait!? You try to psychoanalyze your leader and then imply my machinations could possibly be of lesser importance than something idiotic like this stupid project? You're just as dumb as the people behind this! Listen, I don't *want* to be viewed in any way, because I *am* a villain, and I *am* feared as one! So get with the program, before I break out of these restraints and show you the extent of my abilities!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “The Antarctica Project, right?” He ignores most of what you said.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Wow, big round of applause to the overgrown toaster for growing half a brain! Yes, I don't know how you found out about it, but I really don't care. Is that all you wanted to ask? The name? Real great detective work here, I'm sure you've learned a lot."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “No, I already knew that. Horatius told me what they know. I’m only interested in how this relates to what I asked about. Is this a matter of your view on things? That reality is your point of origin — ‘Earth’ — meaning this must be illusory?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "You really didn't think this through, did you? If I was that skeptical, I would've been calling you guys fake the first time I showed up! You think I *want* to believe this place is fake? It's a dream come true for a villain like me! Two worlds to conquer! No, no, I know this place is all one big fake because I know the asshole behind making it. You see, it's called being important, and thus having connections."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “I see. And who is this creator?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "...Hah! You think I'll be intimidated into revealing the twist that easily!? That information is on a need to know basis! And what you need to know is that once I get control of this silly little reality you call a home, I'm throwing Bern right out as retribution for your treason against me! How do you like that evil scheme, huh?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: Voreverl is electrocuted.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “A need to know basis? Based on what? I do need to know.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "S-So you're... Not all talk, huh...?" she tries to force a smug grin "I can respect that. A good villain should follow through on a threat. Doesn't change how stupid you are for challenging me. You can... keep shocking me all you want, but I'm not telling! He's irrelevant, nothing, a pawn in my grand design! I don't bother letting microbes know about what other microbes to look out for."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Great job with this design, then. Was getting caught part of your plan?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "It's more of a freestyle thing. Like evil jazz. Or normal jazz, that's plenty evil enough. Whatever, the point is that I'm exactly where I want to be! Just wait, the sheer overwhelming force of my presence will intimidate you down! It'll be the perfect showcase of the aura of evil that surrounds me!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
"Voreverl Leocot. I do not like you. I would be caught off guard if it turned out anyone did. But I am different."
He lowers the weapon.
"You are already aware of what Horatius thinks of you. And while Wress is eager to play the peacekeeper, his idealism is fundamentally incompatible with your words. But I can tolerate it. I have a tolerating respect for the actions of this revolutionary group; I would not be here if I didn't. But I hold no meaningful allegiance to them. I was not lying when I expressed a willingness to serve you. As soon as my questions are answered, we can leave, going to whatever it is you're after. The others are likely to be occupied for the foreseeable future."
He punches the wall, creating a Furn hand shaped dent. "*The fact that I am willing to cooperate with your demands should not be taken as an indication that I will not continue to employ the other method of negotiation.*"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl takes a few moments to respond, eyes shifting around the room "...Gweh... Gweheheheh! So that's what this is, then? I get it! You just wanted to run off as my minion this whole time, right? I understand, my villainous charm is quite alluring! You didn't have to act out this whole dramatic interrogation, but I understand, you're too embarrassed about wanting to serve me. Fine then, I'll take your 'deal'. I tell you who's behind this, and you and I get the hell out of here, do I got that right?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "A few steps in between, but yes. Nothing else you should have reason to hesitate in speaking on."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Alright, well here it is! Watch as the villain of the story unveils the truth! The creator of this fake world is a man named John Leiblich! He's my... he... he's... ugh! No, that's not right! That isn't it! John Leiblich is the father of the foolish woman killed by Voreverl Leocot! The existence that they forced on my body back on Earth! So there you have it! I revealed his identity! Satisfied!?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
Furn lifts you (and by extension the chair you are still attached to) into the air with both hands. It seems like he could probably unintentionally break the bones in your shoulders in this pose.

***"YOUR EARTH BODY IS DEAD???"***

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl swallows hard, and begins trying to sputter out a response for a few seconds before finally getting the words out "Wh-whoa there! C-calm down, big guy! I-I was talking, like, y-y'know, metaphorically! I'm perfectly alive there! Not even a zombie or vampire... as cool and evil as that would be... gweh... heh..."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
He shoves you back down on the ground. "Ah. Okay. Fine."

Furn turns upwards to the ceiling. "John Leiblich... a strange name for a god. But were he a mere mortal in the world he came from, I suppose that would be the case." He directs his attention back towards you. "I cannot believe this, but I don't consider it impossible. A mortal can certainly create a complex facsimile of existence with enough skill and time. I would be interested to learn more, but I suppose your awareness of the truth here is also limited."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "How foolish of you, thinking there's anything outside of the knowledge of... uh... well..." Voreverl groans "I guess you're not entirely off base this time. It's not the main villain's job to know how all the technology works anyway, so I'm not embarrassed to say that I haven't yet found out all the details."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
"Okay."

There's silence for a bit.

"What is it you want? I said I would assist you in your goals, but I need to know what they are for that. Is it to gain political power here? To escape back to your home world permanently? Both, somehow?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Politics shmolitics, you're thinking of being evil in the most *boring* way possible! Think of it this way: back on Earth, I'm treated as an absolute force of evil. My very name sends shivers down the spines of children. But here? Well, I just got here, you guys are the only ones with the displeasure of knowing true fear. I'll need to learn a bit more about this place to think of a real plan, but the *goal* is making it so that not a single person can go a moment without that looming sense of dread my evil creates!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "Okay. So it's fame, with the condition that people hate you."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Is it a *requirement* that you phrase things in the lamest way possible? But sure, yeah, you get the idea, I guess."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
"I want to be accurate. Precise. Avoid..." He stares up above, at the ceiling, and though his expression remains unchanging, you almost sense fear from him for a second. "...ambiguity, if possible. Not everyone comes to conclusions the same way you do."

He reaches for the ropes, and, after fumbling with them for a few seconds, just snaps off the back of the chair, freeing you. "I don't want Bern to become infamous as a menace to society if the world Wress is fighting for comes to be. And you happen to look exactly like him when you're here. But that's an issue for some time from now if ever, and I already have a few thoughts on how to resolve that. We can leave this building, so long as we remain quiet."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Honestly, with strength like that, I have trouble believing you'll think of anything worthwhile as a solution, but it might be amusing to hear. And as long it's not too inconvenient, I'll *consider* not ruining Bern's life." Voreverl stands up and stretches out "Gweheheh, I knew I'd escape from those restraints sooner or later. Now, show me the way out, minion!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
He leads you up from the dungeon to the first floor.

“They should all still be on the third floor, but just in case, we’ll take an exit that isn’t the front door.” ((Roll stealth))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: Nobody noticed them. Furn leads you to a ladder down to a mineshaft which very quickly connects back to the surface.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
The opening hatch leading to this ladder is smaller than Furn.

“…I did not anticipate this. You descend first.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "So you knew there was a ladder here but you didn't know its size? Very selective layout information you got there. But sure, a leader must lead." Voreverl climbs down.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
After Voreverl reaches the bottom, Furn smashes through the floor like a gravity assisted Kool-Aid Man.

“Oh yeah.” 




“I just remembered.” He recalled something while falling. That’s why he said oh yeah.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Is it something I'll be interested in? I can't say I care much about hearing every random thought that passes through your head."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Probably not. Are you able to cast *Sending*?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Am I what? Not doing a great job avoiding ambiguity here. Even with my limitless talent as an evil mastermind, I really have no idea what that means."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Ah. No magic on Earth. Right. It’s probably unimportant.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Good to hear it. In that case, no point wasting any more time around this joke of a prison." Voreverl begins heading down the mineshaft.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: They reach the exterior. “…Now what? I suppose we could focus on creating some distance between us and them.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Hmm... Hold on a moment, I need to check something." Voreverl takes out her PDA and looks through it quickly "Ugh, those imbeciles talk so much... Whatever, who cares about that... Ah, this is interesting..." Voreverl puts it away "It appears as if the ones behind this scheme have instructed us to travel to the capital. As much as I loathe to admit it, you know this world better than I do, so what are your thoughts on that?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
He looks down. “It’s the place with the highest density of people, I guess. And the seat of power over the whole land.”

He stares at where the sun is to orient himself, apparently not having a built in compass. “Walking there definitely wouldn’t be the fastest way at this point, though. We’d be better off teleporting. There’s two places that I think we’d be able to do that at without trouble.”
He points to a direction. “Over in that direction is Intuitia. Anyone who can make it in, the guy transports, no questions asked. It would be closer by distance. But…”

He adjusts his arm slightly. “My opinion is that we’d be better off heading this way, to Neko’s tower. They’re not too far apart, but Wress is going to try to go to Intuitia next, probably staying there for a bit. To avoid him, we’d take the other option. Additionally, you may want to talk to Neko. I do not understand her, but I equally do not understand you, and she is incredibly successful at cultivating fame and power. An ‘influencer’ of sorts.”

He turns back to you. “This is the extent of my relevant information at this juncture. I’ll also be straightforward in saying that whenever Bern gets back, I’m going to cooperate with his aims. I would certainly prefer we not engage in some asinine back and forth, though, so I’ll endeavor to avoid one.”

“I’ve stated my preference, but the decision is yours.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl is looking pretty excited now "An influencer!? Oh, this is great! I've been talking about working on my brand for a while now! Gweheheh, you know, maybe I underestimated your cognitive abilities... There has to be some kind of weak point, though. A villain having brawn and brains makes no sense. Whatever, to this 'Neko' we shall go!" Voreverl heads off in that direction.

author.name: legoskelton

messages.content: At some point after a long while of travelling, a figure is visible in the distance. "...We should attempt to avoid them. No normal people would be wandering about around here." Furn quickly looks around for an alternate route.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "No normal person you say? Gweheheh, that just gives us all the more reason to run into them. Be it a hero looking to challenge me, or another villain on my turf, Voreverl Leocot does not back down! A cowardly villain can never strike fear into the hearts of the people!" Voreverl continues walking towards the figure at a normal pace.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
Furn makes a mechanical rumbling sound vaguely analogous to groaning.

The man notices you and quickens his pace until your group and him finally collide. This person is dressed kind of like a cowboy. "Heh. Y'oughta know better than to go walking around the untamed plains alone, kid." This person also has a gun.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Untamed, you say? Don't make me laugh! Maybe to a weakling like you, but for me, everywhere I go is under my command! Maybe if you had any sense of fashion, you wouldn't be so self-conscious as to need to project your own fears onto someone flawless like me!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "Nah. I don't got much of a sense of fashion." He laughs at this one. "Do I look that bad? Suppose I'm just too intimidating to give anyone the chance to slander my appearance most of the time. You're bold, kid." He has his hand   on the gun.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Intimidating? You? Voreverl Leocot is not intimidated by someone so behind the times! What is it you've got in your hand there, some kind of toy? I already know this place is all about magic, not technology, so don't try to trick me into thinking you've somehow developed guns already."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "Well, I certainly didn't make this thing myself. It's served me well, though. It shoots out high energy lead projectiles that can travel straight through flesh. It's quite deadly... if you can successfully hit a shot."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
"Are you going to attempt to shoot us, or is this a theoretical fixation of yours?" Furn asks a rhetorical question. He has not had the best day.

"Agh! Who's there?" The man vaguely points his gun in the direction of Furn. "I knew it wasn't just you, but everything else should've been your belongings, right? Nothing alive..."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Pffft- You hear that? This idiot can't even notice a cosplayer right in front of them, or maybe I'm just *that* intimidating, took up all of your perception. I guess comparing a minion to my belongings isn't inaccurate, though. Whatever, moral of the story is that you're outnumbered, and obviously inferior. What's your play now, huh?" Voreverl takes a step towards the man.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
"Cosplayer?" Furn does not recognize this word.

"Don't fuck with me!  I don't know if you're a ventriloquist or I made some slip-up, but it doesn't matter! I have the luck to take on two people easily! Gamblin' Randy never misses!" ((roll initiative))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
Randy goes first, aiming at what he deems to be the greater threat, Furn. He hits Furn directly in the head with a bullet, which does nothing because the head is made of metal. "Okay! One down!" Randy yells cockily.

It's @Natyobb.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

mentions.name: natyobb
mentions.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: Voreverl takes a step back "Wh- That thing actually... If that was... Gweheheh! S-sorry Randy, but you've angered the wrong mastermind! Voreverl Leocot always protects her minions, so I can throw them away myself later!" Voreverl tries to grapple Randy and take his gun away.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: This fails spectacularly. Randy executes a perfect roll outside of Voreverl's range.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Furn runs in front of Voreverl using his pitiful speed. "This isn't a bluff. That thing will kill you if it hits in a vital enough spot."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Yeah, I know what a gun is, dumbass! I just... I can't back down so early in my career as an Arctican villain! My reputation will be ruined!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "We will not flee. I will simply crush him in your stead."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
"The hell? How are you still alive! What are you?!"

"I am made of metal. You are incredibly foolish."

Randy slightly tilts his head. "Really? Like, an automaton? That talks? I didn't know that was a thing. Your footsteps sounded human, at least."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "...Oh... Oh, don't tell me! This guy's blind, isn't he? Gweh... Gwehahaha! You have a gun as a weapon? And you can't see!? Wow, you are terrible at this! People like you should know their weaknesses and stay out of the way!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
"Heh. Yeah, that's right. If I reveal that later, it can help freak people out, but too early most the time causes people to get overconfident and bluster in. I'm blind as a bat. Haven't been able to see in decades. But I never miss! People's eyes can lie to them, but someone lucky enough will hit every time!"

Randy shoots through the gap in Furn's legs and hits Voreverl in the shin. This crits and does 15 damage.

It's @Natyobb.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

mentions.name: natyobb
mentions.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "Agh! Fuck! Great job crushing him, Furn! Th-this is nothing! I could take twenty bullets to the head and walk it off! What the hell do you even want? You just started shooting before making demands, what kind of villain are you!?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
"What? There's no way. How could a blind man do that? This... is bad. I do not know what's happening. We need to get out of here." Furn's tone is more wavering.

Randy laughs. "Get out of here? With what, a broken leg and a lumbering sloth? Fat chance! The kind of chances I like best. You caught me off guard, y'know, and that's hard to do. Normally I'd do the whole business of threatening you to give me all your gold first, but if I can profit in the end, it's all the same to... m--e...?"

The tip of a blade pierces through Randy's chest. Combat ends. His body falls to the ground. A man behind him stares down at the body. "Nothing personal, kid."

He looks over at Furn and Voreverl. "Who the hell are you?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: ((I hate when this happens))

author.name: legoskelton
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\7324d6b2e5e7b2d85c445c799b852d80-F5E1E.png

messages.content: Voreverl tries her best to stand up straight as if she wasn't just shot in the leg and walks out from behind Furn "G-Gweheheh! So are you our next challenger!? Let's hope you have a little more to offer than a disabled gambling addict! I am Voreverl Leocot! Supreme overlord of all that is evil, and your worst nightmare!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "...Gambling addict, huh? That's a good way to put it." He withdraws his blade from Randy's body and begins searching it. "You understand how much debt this asshole had? He sure is fucking lucky he lived until now. Unless you've got some vendetta against my organization, I don't really give a shit about taking you out." This man is wearing a fedora also this si important appearance info

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: ((this is the best character))

author.name: legoskelton
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\7324d6b2e5e7b2d85c445c799b852d80-F5E1E.png

messages.content: "A vendetta? Unlikely! Anyone weak enough to rely on an 'organization' is clearly so low down the social rung that they don't even register to me!" Voreverl's eyes lower to Randy's body and then shoot back up "B-but, uh, how about I leave you off with a warning this time? Settling a conflict so soon would be quite the lackluster climax!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
"Heh. Whatever, kid. 'If you are talking loudly with others, you have nothing to say.' One of my best quotes."

He raises an eyebrow. "Are you like, good? Don't think that wound is deadly, but you should probably get it treated."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Ugh, you just don't understand... I'm the villain! Don't worry about me! You should be celebrating me being shot, not worrying! Not that this will do anything, I let myself get shot to demonstrate how little of an effect it would have!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "Kinda seems like he totally would've killed you if you didn't happen to have an ally who was bulletproof. Randy's no joke. It's something of a miracle I was able to kill him, really. Imagine if, for every uncertain situation in life or combat based on factors you don't know, you rolled a 20 sided die to determine how favorable the outcome is. This is a guy who gets a 20 every time. In any situation, he'll always be able to get the best possible result." He smirks. "But when faced with opposition as overwhelming as Isador, I guess luck doesn't matter."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Gweheheh, really? That's his big claim to fame? Luck? You know what's better than being lucky? Never putting yourself in uncertain situations to begin with! That's the sign of a mastermind! I had this whole fight planned out, coming prepared with this bullet proof lunk! I'm not just the chess queen, I'm the whole chessboard!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: He tips his fedora. "A victory with lost blood is the folly of Phyrrus." He gets up, seemingly satisfied with his search of the body. "That wasn't even a pre-existing quote. Literally came up with that right now. Not bad. Anyway, I think your plan was pretty lousy if you got shot and then someone stole your kill. Sorry to say, kid."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Your intervention was not needed." Furn.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Yeah, tell him, Furn! We had a whole second phase prepared! Not that I'll tell you what it was, can't have my genius schemes being stolen by an irrelevant commoner. Anyway, we've wasted enough time, I have an empire to cast a shadow of fear over!" Voreverl continues putting in effort to ignore her injury and tries to continue in the direction they were heading.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "Where the hell are you even going? I'll accept you're a criminal, not many others go this kinda route. But I've sure never seen you before, so this definitely isn't your turf. Leaves a bad taste in my mouth attacking someone already injured, but if you want to make trouble for the mafia, I *will* have to kill you."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "You will not succeed. Go home, you obnoxious charlatan." Furn.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Wow, you think really highly of yourself, huh? Like I'd give a shit about some pretend 'mafia'. Look, I don't like other villains stepping on my toes, but as long as you don't get in my way, then fighting you would just be doing a moral good, and I can't have that. So you do your evil business, I'll do mine, alright?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
“Tch. Fine.”

“It is inadvisable to walk with an open wound. Do you want to stop and rest? I could alternatively provide a place for you to sit on my body while I continue walking.” Furn looks over at you.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Hmph, like I said, this wound is nothing to me! I haven't been hindered at all! ...Although, riding a steed into battle does have a certain commanding image, that *is* why I stole that car... Alright, big guy, let me on!" Voreverl attempts to climb onto Furn.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
The attempt is a success. There’s room by his head for a faux-piggyback ride. 

“Good. Had you refused either, I would have been able to cauterize your wound right then and there before you could react. I just thought that was interesting.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Gweheheh, hiding implied threats in casual conversation... you really have learned a lot as a minion of evil! Obviously, I would not stand for such disrespect, but since it didn't come to that, I'll let it slide. We can call this whole little distraction a part of your training for a real battle of wits."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
“Mm.” Furn trudges on ahead.

Isador continues to remain in front of you.

“Why are you still here.” Furn asks this unenthusiastically. 

“I’m going back and heading to my next destination! The better question is why are *you* following *me*!”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Well, well, you might want to be careful there. According to your silly little phrases, you're starting to have nothing to say. Regardless, this path is big enough for the two of us, real villains don't have squabbles over petty disputes like proximity. See that? That's rational, mature judgement. Fitting for a mastermind like me."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
“Hmph.” Isador resigns to the EVIL practice of live and let live. “…You’re heading to *Elvith*, then?”

“Yeah.” Furn says this to prevent Voreverl from having to comment on terminology she has never heard. “To meet with someone. None of your business.”

“I didn’t ask!” Walking in silence continues for a bit. “It isn’t *Intuition Overdrive*, right?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
Furn has the misfortune of registering the set of syllables Intuition Overdrive. “What? Oh. I am unaccustomed to pretending that is a real name someone has. No. We would be going to where he lived if that was our objective.”

“You could’ve arranged to meet somewhere else.”

“We didn’t.”

“Hmph.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Intuition Overdrive..." Voreverl takes another look at #gc to be sure "Looks like Randy isn't the only one manipulating chance, huh? That guy was yapping away in my, uh, communication device while I was blacked out earlier. Gotta say, his name's a bit uncreative, but it has a certain power to it that I respect. Looks like him and Horatius were arranging to meet though, so yeah, no thanks, he has clearly awful taste."

author.name: natyobb

messages.content: “Uh, I dunno. Lot of people in the world. I could give you dirt on Intuition, Neko, Xeltir, some of the royals… about the only person off limits would be my boss.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Oh? Neko, huh? Well, I don't have anything against her, but having an upper hand will certainly be useful. Alright, spill it, what's the gossip?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Well, this one’s a bit of an open secret for people who bother to do research, but Neko’s a pseudonym. Her actual name… is Catarina Praxis, eldest daughter of the royals! Tries to distance herself from that, but not enough to give up on the lingering status entirely.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
“Ghrk! Shut the hell up! How about this, then? She’s a sexual deviant! Into other women! Hooked up with her family’s own servant once!”

Furn responds nearly immediately again. “I didn’t know this. It is instead completely useless information.”

author.name: scipe

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Oh, so you weren't exaggerating when you said you were 'in the know'. Yes, that lame capitalist space rock is my home. You visit it or something?"

author.name: natyobb

messages.content: “Ah.” He looks up. “No. I don’t visit. I haven’t been there in years. But it’s where I was born. Spain.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "...Years? How long ago did this idiotic project start? In any case, can't say I blame you for moving. So far this place beats Earth pretty handily. Just wish I could come by choice."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “I dunno. It already seemed like it was around for a while by the time they involved u…well, anyway, yeah, I’m sure you’re aware this is a simulation or something. Probably. author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I'd hate to be the poor writers forced to write out a thousand years of lore... Except for the parts regarding whatever evil overlords probably ruled, that's classic fantasy stuff. But yeah, pretty soon Voreverl Leocot will harness whatever technology is making this place run for my own evil schemes. Gweheheh, they should've never brought in someone as unpredictable as me."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Yeah, that’s cool. Good luck with that.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "...Hm. You don't seem very concerned about my future takeover. Once I'm on top, who knows, I might be able to delete this place with the flick of a switch. Everything you've built up could crumble!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png
