author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
Voreverl wakes up in a featureless expanse of void. Eric Zeety is there. He looks around.

"...Mhm. I figured."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl remains silent for a few moments, before letting out a scream "AAAAAAAAUUUUGGGHHH!!! Great, wonderful, just what I wanted, back to this death trap! I-I guess it makes sense, this is where I belong, isn't it!? I get to be Bernard Zie again, like I was meant to be! It's all I *can* be now anyway!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "Hey, it's not too bad. You've got, uh, that weird robot, right? He's a good ally."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Oh, yes, the one who's undyingly loyal to my body! What a perfect reminder of how I can never be Voreverl Leocot! Just some pathetic wannabe hero, and a man at that! Could I have failed *more*!?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: Eric laughs. "I'm sorry, but who cares? I mean this is--ngh." His form flickers. "This is the ultimate betrayal from all of reality. A key moment in your arc. Frankly, you should be disappointed it was so minor. You're no more a man than Caesar a republican."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "You don't get it... there is no arc! There is no rise to villainy! Not anymore, not ever! Sure, you can laugh it off because you're the one who still gets to be you! You don't know what it's like... no one does!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
“Please. Don’t go saying things like that.” 

Eric smirks. “Besides… well, just one time I’d like to be a little cheeky. I do know what it’s like. Did you like… think Eric Zeety was my *name*? Like, from the illustrious Zeety family? I can get and appreciate calling me what I express I want to be called, but you never once asked about it.” He laughs. “I guess I’m grateful. Identity’s a tricky thing.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “I took it from a visual novel. It’s kind of embarrassing.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: ((No way…))

author.name: leaskeleton
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\62bf52b0df6d1e519ab5b6b2022be20e-553F3.png

messages.content: "..." Voreverl stares blankly at him, before breaking into a smirk "Pffftt- gwhehahahah! Like, those dating games? That's... that's..." her expression darkens "Sorry, at least you know who you are. But still, that's totally different! A name change? Yeah, big deal! My- No, Voreverl Leocot's body doesn't belong to me! I have to restart from the ground up! I... I've wasted my entire life thinking I could be something I just wasn't!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Pft. Nobody’s in their own body. As far back as the Antarctica thing, I think all the participants were already being moved into identical vessels for convenience. And I don’t think the version of anyone that exists in the other realm can ever be called the same physical thing. It’s… it would also be the same for anyone people chose to bring with them.” Eric slumps over, and switches to a sitting position on the ground. “The body dysmorphia’s a real bitch, sure, but doesn’t this reveal mean you’ve already won? You were planning to take control of both your and Bernard Zie’s bodies, and you’ve done that already.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I... I don't feel in control. The body I use in Arctica, *my* body," Voreverl cringes "spent its whole life controlled by some creep I've never even met! And- and the one on Earth, I was just supposed to make use of it temporarily! It was a mistake that I ever grew up in it! But... but I liked that body... I felt like Voreverl Leocot when I was in it... it's only since I saw myself in my original body that I've started... Ugh! I'm not supposed to feel like this!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “This really could’ve all been timed better.” Eric gives a weary laugh. His image distorts again. “So you take control. You make the way you’re ‘supposed’ to feel your bitch. Do whatever you want. Decimate Bernard Zie in revenge. Or don’t. This is all kind of tangential.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl's eyes light up "Yes... Bernard Zie... it's his fault! He's the one who ruined my life! If he had just stayed in his lane in Arctica... Gweheheh! I just need to get rid of him, and there will be no competition for who gets to be Voreverl Leocot! That's how I take back control!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
He smiles awkwardly. “Whatever works.” Eric crosses his arms, gripping his sides. “Look, I just… you don’t get to have me with you in Arctica. It’s not your fault. There’s no way you could’ve known. But maybe this is fitting.” He coughs, clearing his throat.

“I always wondered how it would come across. When the day came. I think I always knew you’d end up learning at one point. That I’ve just been lying constantly.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl looks concerned and reaches out a hand to try to help him up "Hey, what are you talking about? You're my top minion! Of course you're coming with me to Arctica! I only select winners for my army, so don't give me that quitters talk! Look... whatever it is you lied about doesn't matter! Stop messing around and take this seriously!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: ((Mist Meric))

author.name: leaskeleton
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\62bf52b0df6d1e519ab5b6b2022be20e-553F3.png

messages.content:
“I know. It’s really fucking selfish. You’ve always been way better at being the focus of the scene. I’ve been more than a little jealous at times, being in the background, but it’s fine. That’s my role. And it’s… all out of whack. You’re only supposed to be in this situation if you stomped someone brutally and evilly. None of that wimpy sympathy bait for a villain.”
Eric’s eyes go hazy and unfocused.
“But I’m not really in control of that. I guess I never had as much control as I thought I did.”

He strains himself to focus.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “This is the part where I die.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: ((NOO))

author.name: leaskeleton
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\62bf52b0df6d1e519ab5b6b2022be20e-553F3.png

messages.content: "You- Wh- No! Shut up! Are you insane!? You... you can't be that much of a hypocrite! Tell me to take back control and then just... just up and die on me!? You're joking right!? What about the zoo!? What about all my schemes... I-I can handle them alone, of course, but... Look, just hang on, okay? We can... we can find help in Arctica, whatever's wrong! I'll pull some evil strings! That's what I do!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
“You can… hold onto that. Maybe you can pull something off. There’s a lot of miraculous stuff out there. And you’re pretty miraculous yourself. I’m not doing this to try to hold you back or anything. I just… I want to talk. If I’m not doing anything, I think it gets worse… this void unraveling me, absorbing me into its own.”

Eric’s foot slips, dangling slightly below where you’d infer the ‘floor’ is here.
“Yeah, it sure does. Whoops. You know the funniest fucking part? It’s that I know this can’t be the same both ways. I’m Eric Zeety. You’ve known me for some handful of months as a coworker who is mildly agreeable. But for me…”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
“This past year or so, I— I’m happy. I was, I mean. Y’know. I went through each day excited just for what would happen in the day itself. The idea that I… that someone like me could live that way… it never would’ve come to my mind. Anyone’s.”

He smiles. “You gave that to me even when it was always going to be taken away one day. You’re a real crafty maniac.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “Hey, enough of the sappy nonsense. Let’s get down to brass tacks. What this whole tale’s about. PH, TGP, TAP, GT, all the dumbass acronyms, the queen, Bernard Zie, John Leiblich, Mohammad Avdol, what fucking ever—it’s all a bunch of distractions. They’re the *other villains*. The minor foes you bump off or outlast to show what a big deal you are. The real focus, the protagonist of this story—that’s something else entirely.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “I want to tell you everything I know. That’s how it’s supposed to work. Mysteries are for the detective, not the culprit. You should understand everything from the start. But I think if I tried to spoil everything, I’d be cut short immediately. A premonition. Maybe it’s worth the risk.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “Well, that’s what I’ll ask of you. I’ll hold out. Maybe I can survive through this and serve as your minion again. In exchange… I want you to understand. Not the nonsense of every little world switch, the mechanics of magic, John Leiblich’s name lore. There’s way too much meaningless clutter in this project. I want you to know why you’re here. When you do… I think you’ll be able to win.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “…Okay? It doesn’t matter if you betray me. As long as I can think you will.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl takes a moment, and then nods "...It wouldn't be a proper betrayal unless I played along, now would it? Gweheheh, very well, minion! I, Voreverl Leocot, shall grant you this much! Not out of sympathy, but simply as a pragmatic, villainous decision! I've brought you here to torture the truth out of you, so give it to me, or suffer the consequences!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: He laughs. “Well, here’s one thing. Erica’s agreed to wire you like a billion dollars on Earth if you acknowledge her as the protagonist in the group chat. Just one opportunity you can try to take advantage of.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: ((classic erica))

author.name: leaskeleton
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\62bf52b0df6d1e519ab5b6b2022be20e-553F3.png

messages.content:
“Beyond that, uh…” He grimaces. “Ugh. TGP’s Dextrum, PH is Culbasko, SOUL is Oppineta… Wyrd and Zita Praxis are one and the same. Third guy involved with TAP is Sheeval Deltent, but he’s dead now. Oh, and Avdol—“
Eric screams in agony. “Fuck! Shit. Ghrk. There’s only so much that can happen.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
Eric’s more floating than resting on any clear surface by this point.
“Isidora, our boss - I think the TAP guys bought her out and that has something to do with what happened the first day. Take care of the flamingos till I’m back.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “Pretty much everyone had at least one accomplice they knew that kept things running smoothly and set things up at their physical location.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
“It’s… it really hurts. It’s not even a physical pain it’s… my soul itself, my *sense* of self… everything’s being torn apart.” 
He squints.
“I’m not stopping until the last moment. You know about the Bernard Zie body switch, but that’s not the only time a child’s life was saved with this world switching stuff. The queen’s daughter Eulogia—she—it was sort of similar. Haruka Tanaka might know about that? I forget the logistics of everything. That’s the quasi-accomplice Rikarasu knew. She’s not actually related at all to George Tanaka, as far as I know. That’s a guy in Arctica. One of the original—oh, yeah, this part. There were originally twelve participants. Six from each place. You’re familiar with like, nine? Except Joliene doesn’t count, she was a last minute replacement for Eric Dextrum.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
“Maybe this is just a distraction. I don’t know what else to say. There’s so much I could say, so much I can’t. Even if I was free to do anything, could I find the words? I don’t think I… I wouldn’t know how.”

He shivers. “The participants who die, as well as certain people involved with the project, they end up having something to do with this idea of *observers*—“ The void begins encroaching on Eric Zeety, burying his body. “Well, I think I made a pretty economic use of time. …Goodbye, Voreverl Leocot. It was all a lot of fun.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl was straining herself in thought trying to follow the exposition, but snaps back when she hears that and tries to force a grin "Th-that's it, huh... I... I guess this is what victory f-feels like...! Gwehah! Goodbye Eric Zeety! I cast you away as a stepping stone so that I can face superior foes with my own power!" She casts her eyes down, avoiding his gaze "And thank you... you're the best minion I could ask for."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
Eric doesn’t have anything else to say.

And then he’s gone. Hopefully Voreverl can get over this. He was really just a joke character.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl hears footsteps behind her.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: A man who looks like this emerges. “Excuse me, but, what exactly is all this?”

author.name: scipe

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
You wake up in what looks like a fancy rich person bedroom. Furn's in the corner of the room, hunched over.

"Hey."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl takes a moment to respond "Yeah... Hey, minion." Voreverl does a quick glance over of the room before sighing "So, uh, gweheheh, where am I?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
"Oh, it's you. Dammit. We really can't... there's a lot going on right now. I came here to get away from that drama." He gets up.
"We're in a house in the middle of nowhere. No idea who built it, but this is some government testing zone."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Right, okay..." Voreverl is silent for a few more seconds "Sorry, there's a lot to process right now. Revelations only the true villain of the story is allowed access to, grand reveals about conspiracies you couldn't even imagine, that kind of thing. You know, have to... sort things out."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "Hey, I don't mind if you need to take some time to sort things out. I probably do too."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I don't need your approval. Besides, whatever you're sorting out can't be nearly as important as my evil schemes! Don't try to place our problems on the same level."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "Yeah, sure, okay."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "...Ugh! Fine! What are you sorting out, minion? I can't have you being useless when we get into trouble. It's a leader's responsibility to crush her minion's problems!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "Someone sold... ah, wait, you wouldn't even know we met with them. This is annoying." Furn grunts. "If you care to figure out the situation, follow me. Or don't. Just don't leave this building without letting me know, is all I'm that invested in."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: He leaves the room.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl follows him "For future reference, Voreverl Leocot does not need to report to anyone, nor does she follow anyone! I've simply decided to head in the same direction as you for the moment."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
As they head further into the building, conversation (or argument) becomes audible.

In what looks like a dining room, a large group of people is present, including Jorge (Jorge), Wress Hifele, and Horatius Kyodu tied to a chair. Next to Horatius is a skittish looking young woman, who is not tied up but is being closely watched by some armed rebels.

Wress sees Furn enter. "Oh, you two are here."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: A smirk rises to Voreverl's face, and she throws out her arms "That's right! Your glorious leader, Voreverl Leocot, has returned! I thought you minions useless enough to ditch you earlier, but it would appear my inferior half disagreed. While I'm here, I'll give you a taste of my brilliance by settling whatever foolish dispute is taking place!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
Wress lets out a pained sob. "Oh, god."

Horatius chuckles. "This should be good."

Furn stares ahead blankly. "In essence, Horatius is some other guy right now. Same way your body keeps switching around. The girl there -- don't remember her name -- she fucked up and gave information about our location to an unknown source. I think these two facts are unrelated, but I've lost track of the discourse, really."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Oh? Gweheheh, that's interesting. When I saw Horatius tied up here, I was going to order them to be tortured in the dungeons as punishment for whatever crime they foolishly committed! But this... This is a golden opportunity! All in favor of the death penalty?" Voreverl raises her hand.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
"No." Wress.

"That hardly seems fair. I'm not Horatius." Horatius.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Fair? You seem to not know who you're talking to. Normally I'd give a big introduction speech, but I'm not in the mood. Listen, whoever you are, you're going to die here! And then we'll discover just what happens to the transfers when one party dies! Will Horatius go with you, or will they just stay over on Earth? You should be happy I'm letting you be a footnote in the backstory of my rise to power!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
"I see. You've a taste for blood now, then? Go ahead. I can't imagine any greater honor than being killed by you." Horatius smirks.

"What? No! That's not happening!" Wress.

Furn sits in the corner.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Wress... You followed my orders without much fuss last time. What's changed? This body snatcher has agreed to my plan, so why can't you get with the program!? Furthering my goals is so much more important than whatever foolish rationale you're upholding here!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
"I'm not fucking killing Horatius!" Wress snarls at you. The room quiets down for a moment.

A young woman in a maid outfit walks in, followed by Erica Furuda, who Voreverl does not know is named Erica Furuda. 

"All of you should leave here immediately." The maid says this.

messages.content: Um, okay, I guess I’m supposed to…

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
Voreverl Leocot is ascending a staircase accompanied by a few other people.

“Are you sure you’re up for this…? Don’t want to, I don’t know, prep for a little longer?” The large mechanical being asks this.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Gweheheh, have you learned nothing? Preparations are for the minions! An evil warlock shall always be ready, no matter the circumstance! Imagine if the heroes burst down the throne room door, only to find the villain still in the middle of filing paperwork for raising taxes. It would be embarrassing! Laughable! Pathetic! The opposite of Voreverl Leocot! You should be asking if they're prepared for *me*!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
“Fact.” Gratia affirms this. 

Katrielle trails behind the other three, behaving in a way that could be described as sly.

Furn speaks again. “I just… I mean, there’s a threshold at some point, right? When this sort of multiclassing becomes worth it, I don’t know if it’s enough to…” His vague whining trails off. Seems he wants to object but doesn’t have a real reason he can explain.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "It's clear you have your doubts, minion. But no matter! I shall crush all of your hesitancy through a demonstration of my raw magical power!" Voreverl's ascent of the stairs has a renewed spring in her step.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
“How many of these fucking steps are there?! What, is this building 80% empty space?” Katrielle loses it.

Right on time, a door is reached.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Patience is a virtue, minion number two. Excellent work not making use of it!" Voreverl grabs the door handle "The first chapter of my rise to power has finally reached its climax! First this tower, then the world, then Bernard Zie! All shall crumble before my might!" Voreverl slams the door open.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: The room is something like an office. A single woman sits at a desk, jotting something down. She glances up. “Oh. Someone actually made it here.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Your surprise is far from misplaced. No other challenger could possibly have the raw power, resolve, and evil genius required to match up to the greatest feats of Voreverl Leocot! But enough talk! I didn't come here simply to brag. The hope of the masses has gone unbroken for long enough! Are you prepared to stand as their representative, being crushed underneath the heel of my campaign of evil!?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
She opens and closes her mouth several times, considering how to respond.

“What are you even talking about?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Gweheheh, so that's how we're playing it? Feigning ignorance so you can catch me off guard? Or perhaps you're merely the secretary to the real champion of this establishment. Voreverl Leocot cares not either way, but spare me the theatrics, my victory over Jill Bobs cannot be delayed a moment longer!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Yes, that’s me. Okay, I understand, you’re the upstart… What was your name, again?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "...Is this a test? A magical spell to hold me captive in your voodoo curse if I utter my own name for a third time in your presence!? You think you're so smart, don't you!? But Voreverl Leocot cannot be tricked by the likes of you!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
“Oh, that’s you. Yeah, it’s coming together.” She closes a folder. 
“I have no interest in fighting you. So I won’t. Very few people interest me.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "H-huh? But that's your job, right!? You, the hero, resting on your laurels, fight against me, the villain conquering this tower as a show of strength! You can't just say no! That's... that's like the whole premise of this thing! I climbed so many stairs!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
She smirks. “I’m not a hero.” 
She shakes her head, thinking things over for a moment.
“But… I could lead you to one. I’m willing to provide a final foe for you, and official recognition of your victory if you can make it through that. This is a well established conclusion.”

Furn makes a vague breathy noise with his not-lung-having voice source. “Lead her to one?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Gweheh? An interesting proposal. Very well, I shall accept this. A final battle against one as unmotivated as yourself would simply be dull, and quite the poor show of strength. On with it, then! Reveal the hero's location to me, or I will wring it out of you!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
“Okay.” She stares at the other three. “All negligible in terms of strength… I’ll just send them away too.”

“Wait, what?” Furn jolts forward.

Voreverl is teleported elsewhere. ((The session ends.))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
Voreverl can barely see anything. After a few seconds, Furn lights up the area by doing that thing he does where there’s fire in him. 

The room contains a confusing device rooted to the ground with pipes and tubes. Visible within a transparent vessel is some blueish white material with the consistency of flame. It seems to glow, but it did not give off light. 

This square section of whatever greater area you are in has four distinct hallways leading out of it, all of which immediately hit a wall and turn. The whole thing seems vaguely labyrinthine. Audible from essentially all directions is rumblings and mechanical whirring, but the loudest is a rhythmic pulse that seems to be below your feet.

Katrielle is already casually leaning back against a wall, annoyed more than surprised. Gratia has fallen face flat onto the ground somehow, and slowly gets back up.

What will you do?

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: ((it appears... there might be four escapes))

author.name: zzazz
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\00e5cb55aacbe3824e8b8a9d53aac811-1CCD0.png

messages.content: "Gweheheh... so, this is the dungeon of a Hero then? Quite the dingy place, absolutely no style, you can tell why they didn't become a villain. Some people just can't help but take the easy way out." Voreverl shrugs her shoulders, then gestures to her minions "But this is no time for dallying! Four hallways, and four of us, it's clear what this hero wants us to do. Separate, split up, divide our numbers! Those are the rules of the game. But Voreverl Leocot does not play by the rules!" Voreverl takes out her shortsword and slams it down onto the curious device, attempting to break it.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: ((Roll))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: ((NAT 20 BABY))

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: ((I hate you so much.))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
“Huh?” Gratia lets out the first thing to be said by any of the non-participants here just as Voreverl slams her short sword into a thing that she doesn’t know what it does. The glass is strong enough to securely store and transfer its contents while leaving it visible for inspection, but it seems a direct attack wasn’t considered. The glass shatters.

It is self-evidently not solid, and an observer could tell mere milliseconds after the container is shattered that this is no liquid, seeming completely unaffected by gravity.

Yet gaseous would also feel an inappropriate descriptor, as the particles and clumps jolt around every which way, some zigzagging and oscillating near where they already were, while most jolt immediately out of the area. One bumps into Voreverl and phases through her, creating a vague sense of discomfort. Furn is knocked off his feet by a couple.

Before any of this can even register, the entire building begins shaking violently. Slightly after it is able to register, a painful alarm begins to sound.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “Wow. I’m in awe, evil genius.” Katrielle groans, and picks one of the exits to run out of.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Uh..." Voreverl clears her throat and tries to yell over the alarm "Let this be a lesson, minions! Never let your enemy near the weakest point of your defenses! Keep it hidden, bury your kryptonite deep underground and out of sight! This battle is won before it even began! This is the power... of Voreverl Leocot's art of war!" Voreverl runs out of the same exit as Katrielle.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
As you catch up to her, Katrielle is using a gun (she has a gun) to blow the head off of some armed automaton (it’s not Furn).

“Wow! I guess these are guards??? Feels like we’re doing this backwards! Very twisted! Very cool!!!” Gratia yells.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I only have so much ammunition. You all will need to pull your weight if there's any more of those things."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

attachments.url: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\Kir_a19_majime1-1DF94.webp

messages.content: ((This sprite is not a spoiler for Umineko. She holds a gun under very telegraphed and relatively mundane circumstances.))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Do not fear, minions! Well, don't fear these foolish guardians! Fear me instead! For my new warlock powers can deal with any threats thrown our way! The rest of you can consider yourself mere lucky audience members!" Voreverl continues running down the hall.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: She does. ((Roll Constitution))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
Voreverl manages to stay upright from a particularly large tremor. Gratia falls comically but uses a technique reminiscent of the *zuì quán*, also known as Drunken Fist, to segue this into a roll and keep moving. Nobody else falls.

Though the hallway bends and splits, it never seems to lead into a dead end, and the running continues.

The three stop in front of an actual door.

"Wait... uh..." Gratia mumbles.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
Katrielle tries the door.

"Tch. Locked."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

attachments.url: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\Kir_a24_nayamu1-DC81D.webp

messages.content: She steals Gratia's hairpin, a facet of her design never mentioned before now, and gets to work on forcing the door open.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Gweh, what a boring obstacle. Leave the grunt work to the grunts, I say. I suppose this allows us a moment to scheme while we wait." She points at Gratia "You, minion number three, what have you learned from my brilliant strategies employed here? Have you internalized this important lesson in evil lair interior design?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
"I think! Uh, there's definitely things you can do to stop people from just teleporting into your base.... so, pretty amateur stuff here. And leaving it exposed and only contained by glass? Crazy. Uh, where's the... big one?" She looks around.

Katrielle unlocks the door and moves on.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Indeed, minion, excellent observations on the failures of..." Voreverl processes Gratia's observation on the Furn shaped lack of Furn "Why did you take so long to speak up!? That was my most powerful minion!" Voreverl looks between the door and the direction they came from "Leaving that rusted tin man to die would be rather evil..."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Um, I guess…” she ponders. “…Yeah, definitely! If he’s really powerful, he’ll find his own way through anyway. That’s what I was thinking.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Indeed! I don't allow weaklings into my ranks. If he dies here, he didn't deserve to work under the banner of Voreverl Leocot's evil empire in the first place!" Voreverl grits her teeth and resumes running after Katrielle.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: The door Katrielle opened leads into a small shaft with a ladder. She’s already cleared it by the time you step in.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl Leocot climbs the ladder.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
((What a thrill.))

She emerges from a small hatch in the floor, at which point it becomes more clear what is going on.

To one side, a tower is visible. It seems to spiral up, to have layers, and at least four higher floors. The stone floor you are on is made of the same general material. On the other side…

There’s a scenic outlook of some grassy plains, viewed from far above the land. But the view keeps shaking.

Voreverl Leocot has destroyed the engine of a ship she is on.

Katrielle stares off into the distance, expressionless.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl looks on in awe for a moment, before curling her mouth into a grin "Gweh... Gweheheh... Gwehahahahahah! This is better than I could have imagined! Imagine the looks of those fools on the ground when this ship comes crashing down! Oh, that will be an act of terrorism they'll never forget! All we have to do then is announce that it was Voreverl Leocot responsible! Oh, oh, how much time do we have left? Can we pilot this thing to a city?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “…I guess there were rumors, yeah. The Groverfield home should be a ways north of here. And I’d long heard tellings of a castle in the sky, one that served as a bad omen. I wonder what Jill actually intended for us…?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
Gratia emerges from below.
“Wow….” She admires the view.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl scoffs "Who cares what that coward intended? That's your problem, minion, you're too locked down by society's rules. Voreverl Leocot has reclaimed this situation, all that matters now is maximizing collateral damage."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
“Are you &$¥§?” Katrielle uses an ableist slur exclusive to Arctica. “I don’t mean that to be insulting, it’s a real question. You ever talk to a shrink or whatever?” She sits down on the floor.
“I think it would explain… everything. Not just about you.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Hmph, such a foolish question. Voreverl Leocot is the final evolution of the human race... No, she's an evolution beyond it! A mere psychologist couldn't even understand the first layer of my inner machinations! It'd be like... like the Joker and Harley Quinn. I'm an impenetrable wall!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Yeah, cool. Thanks for answering. You seem pretty calm right now. Would you be fine if you died here? Suits a villain to be defeated in the end, right?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Gwehuh? That's... that's not right at all! First of all, no one is here defeating me, villains don't just self-destruct. And second, any villain who *does* get defeated is feeble! Just a... just a stepping stone on the path to the real big bad, me, Voreverl Leocot! My story doesn't have an ending, of course I won't die here!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
“I see. You’d better start making your peace, then. Or I could kill you, if having a person do it is a sticking point.”
She starts shaking. It escalates into a full blown cackle. Gratia tenses up and takes position by Voreverl’s side.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Katrielle calms down slightly. She turns around to actually face you. "What kind of sick joke is this? How long has it been?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

attachments.url: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\Kir_a24_nayamu1-74814.webp

messages.content: "I've shifted around and crossed the country before coming all the way back. I've been sent to other worlds. And I still can't escape him. That's all I'm ever going to be allowed to be, right? I'm his mother. I don't *get* to leave. Even when he's gone, he's not really gone, is he? You're literally the exact same, the status as a nutcase and all. I just latched onto you as someone I could more easily and freshly take advantage of. Someone I wasn't even expected to care about."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

attachments.url: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\Kir_a14_majime1-83DA9.webp

messages.content: "Yes, that's right. I took advantage of him. He was mentally feeble. He actually saw me as a mother. He loved me. He still does, if nothing's changed. And I never deigned to correct his misunderstanding. Who knows how much more screwed up he became all because of that? So go ahead, kid. Take your revenge. I've been ready for a long time. If I can't win, this is the next best thing."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

attachments.url: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\Kir_a14_warai1-3FE16.webp

messages.content: Voreverl looks baffled "What the fuck are you talking about? Look lady, I don't have any revenge to take, I'm above such superficial motivations. Go resolve your mother-son bonding issues on your own, or don't, I don't give a shit. It's none of my problem. From my experience, the last thing a kid wants is a shitty mook of an underling back in their life as a parent." Voreverl groans "I can't believe I have to deal with this kind of incompetency. Where's the emotionless toaster oven when you need him."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "...I see. I was... caught up in the moment. I guess I'll just let you do whatever it is you think you're doing. I can live with leaving this outcome up to your judgement."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

attachments.url: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\Kir_a24_nayamu1-EFB4B.webp

messages.content:
She turns back around to stare at the landscape. 
"...Wyrd, huh? Haha. I guess now I see what you meant..."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
A young, moderately attractive woman nobody recognizes jumps down from a higher floor.
"Who the *fuck* are you????"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: She directs this primarily to Voreverl, but its a general comment.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl is a bit surprised but tries to not let it show "You... you must be the hero I've heard nothing about! Welcome... to the end of your story! For you have come face to face with none other than Voreverl Leocot! Conqueror of worlds! Scourge on society! A plague on all that is righteous! From the piece of food that gets stuck in your teeth to the meteor that wiped out the dinosaurs, all evil in the world pales in comparison to me! The origin of immorality! I am evil itself!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
She stares at you silently for a few seconds.
"Go... to the top floor. The one you're probably looking for is there. Do not follow me."
The woman, left unidentified, runs off to a different part of the ship.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "..." Voreverl slumps forward in disappointment "Ugh, a perfect introduction wasted. Whatever, I've got a bottomless supply of them. Onwards to the climactic battle, minions!" Voreverl goes to ascend the tower.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
There are automatons of all shapes and sizes preoccupies with strange tasks, but none seem designed for combat like the one Katrielle blew the fuck up. A few seemingly try to approach you, but none are fast enough, except one that Gratia just kind of pushes over and it is unable to right itself (It is a little funny.) As there are only two people who generally do not conflict and are both unpleasant and evil, there isn’t really very interesting conversation during this!

Voreverl is given reason to pause at the penultimate floor, however. The bodies of “Fainda Shinjitsu” and Viotto Entenmann are lying on the floor. Gratia does not understand the significance of this. Voreverl doesn’t either, but she at least has reason to be particularly confused by this.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl recoils in disgust from the sight of Viotto "That delusional nutcase is here? Good thing we're blowing this place to hell. Although..." She walks over to Fainda's body and tries to kick it awake "Hey! No sleeping on the job! You've been avoiding your post as... Whatever evil role I assigned to you for long enough!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “You know ‘em, boss?” Gratia stares at the lady, who is not waking up.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Barely. She was one of the more intelligent minions I've come across... though a bit too questioning of my authority. I doubt anyone will miss her, so it wouldn't be particularly evil to leave her for dead. We can take her with us if we have time." Voreverl leaves the body and continues to the next floor.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
Gratia stops briefly to stare at them some more, then follows after Voreverl.

The top floor could be considered not a “floor” at all, depending on definition. It has no roof. So I suppose it is the roof? Regardless.

There is a hunk of scrap metal, and various bits of machinery, including some figure facing toward the horizon. There's some complicated looking machinery in a small slightly enclosed area, with an elf woman pounding on the controls.

The two of them are spotted immediately by a mostly metallic golem vaguely in the shape of a human woman, who shoots off to the elf without delay.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "So, the hero has a rust bucket minion of her own. A shame we had to leave Furn behind, he could've acted as the evil opposite... Oh well, we'll make do with what we have. Gratia, deal with the cannon fodder." Voreverl makes a vague dismissive gesture towards Gratia.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
Gratia sighs, and runs after the robot running after the woman. They end up catching up at the end of that journey.

The woman at the controls turns around and roundhouse kicks a body hard enough that it flies back to Voreverl, but thankfully (?) for her, it's the robot. This causes Gratia to stand still where she was, incredibly confused.

The elf woman exits the cockpit, shoving Gratia to the side. She walks up to Voreverl, her gaze frigid and impenetrable. She stands tall. Elegant. Undisputed monarch of a kingdom of one.

"Who is this?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl cracks her knuckles "Alright, let's do this. You want to know who I am? Gwehah! The fact that you don't already know is a sign of your failure as a hero of this land! The greatest villain of all time has risen up right under your nose, and you're powerless to stop me! Look at your vessel, falling apart by my hand! Your robotic servants useless in the face of my sheer power! Who am I? Who am I?! I am Voreverl Leocot, and you're nothing but the sloppy seconds of yesterday's news!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "I see... yes, I see. Are you familiar with this vessel, then?" She has a slight smile pasted over absolute rage.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "UNAUTHORIZED ENTRANTS LOCATED -- NO PRIOR CONT" The robot speaks while slowly getting back up, and the woman slaps it on the head to shut it up.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "As if. I don't spend my time researching fools like you. Coming here and destroying your property... I don't need a reason to do that, let alone knowledge of what I'm destroying. I'm a villain, so if I see something, I'll find a way to break it. Leave an irreversible scar in the shape of the name Voreverl Leocot."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "I see, I see. Villain... thank you for introducing yourself. It is an uncommonly seen level of clarity among your people. I will do the same."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
"My name is Nerissa Titinius. I am here for the sake of a quest that began long before you were born and will continue past your death. My ascent will reach the heavens, where I will take my place among angels and the heroes of yore carved into the stars."

She looks down at the robot. "You are an incredibly delightful foe in terms of emotional resonance, Leocot. I would be the hero, yes? I'm only repeating your words, but I certainly agree. And a hero is nothing without a flaw to overcome. Your presence is a result of my own lacking. I tolerated the presence of the vulgar races on *my ship*, on the last thing entrusted to me... and I am now poised to pay the ultimate price. A compelling threat!"

The temperature lowers. "What did you do, specifically? It seems to be engine damage. I also saw the little urchin who arrived with you. Are others aboard?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl's expression reeks of amusement "You don't seem to quite understand the position you're in. I have information you want? Well, you'll just have to wring it out of me. Gwehah, as if. Listen, I can applaud your ambition, you're in this game for the right reasons. Notoriety, the status of a legend, ascending above humanity itself! I can respect you, but you made one fatal error... you chose heroism instead of villainy. And the good guy always loses. You want your quest to continue after today? Tough luck, this is where you meet your end."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
"Pff. Hahah..."

It is snowing. The sun, close to crossing the horizon anyway, is no longer visible.

"O**HO**HO*HOHO*HO***HOHO__HAAAAA__***!" She covers her mouth, and the weather swells with her emotional instability.

"My word! Such boldness. But believe me. If I die, it will be from an antagonist befitting my status. Not a *vassal*. Did Exevel die to the ogress? Was the mermaid princess fell by a stray cat? Calm yourself! You are not here burdened with winning. You are here to teach me a lesson, and you have done so. I thank you, truly."

She does a curtsy.

"The chaos and setback of my dear heirloom having to run on fumes for some time is a fine price to pay. But I am clever. We are not plummeting outright at this point because I have sealed the basement. Some of the energy did not escape, and is being idly if inefficiently processed. An act of desperation, but it will hold for some time. And to truly tide us over until I repair containment, you have brought to me a bare minimum of two souls! I feel almost patronized by the lack of subtlety with which my proper path forward is conveyed to me. Thank whatever false deity you worship, Leocot! You and your kin will become part of something greater than you have any right to."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
Voreverl blankly stares at her for a moment, pondering something "So that's it..." She spits on the floor "Damn Jill Bobs tricked me... You're not a hero at all. Running a device on human souls... It's... Genius! And it's wasted on you! Someone who doesn't even understand that this makes you just another dime a dozen villain! Ugh! We were so close! Your pride, your demeanor, your assumption that somehow you would be more important than me in *any* universe! It would have been so satisfying to kill you if you'd just kept your trap shut!"

Voreverl takes out her shortsword unenthusiastically "Whatever. I shouldn't have expected a climactic battle with an audience of one. I'll kill you, no one will care, and I'll find a real hero."
