It is somehow really awkward and quiet now, and Gratia is still  dead looking, and the ship is still collapsing.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: ((We do not have to go I know in a different server you seemed caught off guard that this was happening))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Gweh... Gweheh... GWEHAHAHAH! Yes! My metallic minion, finish off this fool not worthy of witnessing the true power of Voreverl Leocot! Do you see? Do you understand the machinations at play here!? I wasn't just focused on fighting you, I was summoning a trump card! There are cogs within cogs of my Machiavellian machine of evil!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
“So this thing also intends to interfere?” Nerissa.

“I suppose. Is this, uh, the guy?” He looks at Voreverl.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl kind of dejectedly kicks at the ground "She's *a* guy, I guess. She's no hero! Just some random other unimportant villain that intends to stop my reign of terror! But yes, I do believe Jill Bobs sent us here to kill her. So, get on it."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
“I am a hero. Obviously. Why would a self-proclaimed villain be honest?”

Furn smolders. “Okay, but that would just mean I have even more reason to fight you.”

“I don’t care about that. I only care about principles. You should not operate under delusions in your goals.” Nerissa sighs. “I believe your comrade is under a fundamental misunderstanding caused by ineptitude.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Oh, yeah? Well, your flying fortress is undergoing a fundamental failure due to *your* ineptitude! You don't get to be a pathetic delusional shut-in whose only friends are robots and then criticize *me*! Actually, no one gets to criticize Voreverl Leocot!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
“I suppose I should have safeguarded against teleportation. That illustrates nothing, though. Heroes aren’t infallible. Not from the start, anyway. No one would read stories if they were.”

“I’ve realized I don’t actually care about whatever this is.” Furn attempts to rush Nerissa with his incredibly slow self. This fails, and she knocks him back a few feet. Her heart just doesn’t seem to be in this one.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl throws up her arms in frustration "*Really*? That's the best you've got!? You're giant! You're made of metal! How are you being beaten by someone other than Voreverl Leocot!? She's not even, like, metal-bending you or whatever! Just crush her!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
“I’m a little woozy.” Furn is slow to get up.

“It’s horribly inefficient, you know. I could probably power this entire vehicle for days with the energy wasted to take a step were the means to conversion only available for me.” Nerissa looks at Voreverl while saying this, chiding her.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "...What? I mean, uh, gweheheh! Yes! Inefficient energy is yet another one of Voreverl Leocot's evil schemes! Solar? Wind? Hydro? Foolish! I'll leave the environment in a state of ruin! And, and then charge for breathable air! Be terrified by my blatant disregard for efficient energy use!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
“No, it’s just stupid. You are wasting your own resources. You’re stupid.”

“Air pollution actually got solved a few years back. You can just purify it with minerals, or something. Innovative stuff.” Furn launches an orb of flame at Nerissa.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Oh come on! Polluting the air is... it's every child's dream! It's *the* villain plan! Destroy the world, but leave just enough left to support life. As long as humanity went on, every breath they take would remind them of me! Voreverl Leocot!" Voreverl droops her shoulders "Whatever. I've got thousands of plans. No used crying over pasteurized milk."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: Nerissa’s dress is singed, pissing her off. “Like your amazing plan to take this vessel down? The one you stand to benefit from in no way? Which would kill you anyway were it to succeed? That level of competence? Must have taken quite some time to think of that many.” She kicks Furn, which doesn’t actually do anything to him.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Gweheheheh... You really don't know anything do you? Of course I'm not that shortsighted! I'm an evil genius! I happen to be traveling with a woman capable of using teleportation magic. We'll simply kill you and leave. As for what I gain... I gain the death of this symbol! The greatest terrorist attack in decades! A crumbling, crashing, flaming wreckage falling the ground! What better to represent the start of the age of Voreverl Leocot!?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “What woman? *That* one?” She points to Gratia, a diversion of attention that allows Furn to wallop her in the face.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Of course not. Keep your jokers face down, as I say. Gratia here is nothing but a meat shield, and maybe comedy relief. Every evil empire needs a... court jester..." Voreverl struggles a bit to get those last words out.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “I have no need for jokers!” She sets up a defensive barrier. “You’re quite like the fool tarot yourself, Leocot! Your outer side conceals your lack of value!”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: ((My entire life has led to this message.))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Lack of value, you say? Gweheheh, you know, I compared the worth of your attacks to that of a penny earlier, but perhaps that was an insult to pennies. Abraham Lincoln may have taken on the role of a villain, but after accidentally ending slavery, he failed at even that. You, though... You couldn't even bumble your way into a heroic deed! You've enslaved not only human souls, but a whole crew of robots to do your bidding! You're a tyrant, just like me!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
“This is absurd. Was the Emperor of days gone by a tyrant simply for commissioning the construction of monuments without providing the workers compensation? Of course not. And I am purely more noble; I toil over the well being of these pathetic things, and I extol the glory of my collaborators.” She sighs. “Ideally, I *would* be able to receive direct confirmation of their consent, but such a path is unfortunately not viable.”
Furn is punching the barrier a bunch like that one Metal Gear Rising gif 

“And the mechanical ones! As if an object could present some ethical question. The useless cretin Fema who fell down there doesn’t have a *soul*. She’s a girl without a heart who I still have spent hours and hours on the upkeep of, just like all of my crew. You’re the only one I’ve seen screwed up enough to bind actual life to a facsimile of a person!” She grimaces at Furn.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I did wha-" Voreverl cuts herself off, and a smug grin fills her face "Ah! Of course! My disgusting creature! My Frankenstein! My abomination against the sanctity of life itself! As an inferior villain, you must be disappointed you didn't think of it first! But of course you didn't! For I, Voreverl Leocot, am the only villain brilliant enough to create a being as revolting as this!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
“Don’t push it.” Furn grunts.

“I mean, it’s disgusting. Just an abomination. I feel an overwhelming urge to know more… to avoid such horrors! For instance, how was it done?! Did you concoct it artificially, or transplant the soul of something alive? Why did you see fit to add more than one? How could anyone ever hope to stabilize a—”

“Wait, hold on.” Furn stops punching the barrier. He didn’t seem to be making much progress. “What are you talking about? I’m only one guy. I might not know who that was before being me, but it’s still just the one.”

“Your ignorance astounds. Though I suppose being able to ‘know’ at all is a miracle for you. There’s about three. All bunched up. I can see with my eyes because they are special and better than everyone else ever.”

Furn is silent, and Nerissa busy storing energy for some reason or another. “Wait, is *that* what happened? Why I suddenly stopped being able to…”

He suddenly turns to Voreverl. “Hey, wait a minute! You left me for dead! What the hell is wrong with you?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Well, that's... Gweh... You see..." Her eyes start darting around, before she clenches her fists and takes a breath "...You simply outlived your usefulness as a minion. Knocked around and left behind by a simple engine explosion? Gwehah! If that did you in, then you were never strong enough to assist me in the slightest! And what better demonstration of evil is there than kicking a weak character while they're down!?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
“Oh, sure. Well, I wouldn’t want to get in your way. Go ahead! Defeat her! I’ve shown my pitiful limits already.” Furn sits down.

“Do you two need… a moment? I don’t understand what this is.” Nerissa is still within her ABSOLUTELY SAFE ZONE.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Voreverl Leocot does not need filler arcs! If Furn's feelings are hurt, then his lack of skin simply wasn't thick enough! No, actually, it was exactly thick enough! Because it showed off how evil I am! Gweheheh!" Voreverl looks back and forth between Furn and Nerissa a few times before clicking her tongue "Of course, I could show off my power as a villain here, but I already did that plenty... before you got here! Now, I'll... Yes, I'll *intimidate* you into fighting for me! You won't dare to slack off ever again!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
“No. No, I think this is it. We had a good thing going, Voreverl. We had Wress. We had Katrielle. We had the potential for asynchronous collaboration. We had some good progress on all these mysteries. But you just had to go and screw it all up, one after the other, huh? You, and your pride, and your ego. Well, I can take pride myself in being the end of the line. The final betrayal of the legendary Voreverl Leocot. Nice ring to it.”

“Ach! DeodanaFAEX!” Nerissa glances to the side, then lets her guard down and sprints back to the smaller control station.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Th-that''s..." Voreverl glances around nervously "But... no! I'm... I'm not legendary yet, I haven't even started... No, of course I have, I'm the greatest villain to ever live! I... Can I die here... No... I haven't even..." Voreverl grabs her head and her stance starts to waver "Eric! Eric! I need to find Eric again! He knows what to do! He... I'll take back my life! I have to! Get out of my way! Everyone get out of my way!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
Furn tackles Voreverl… and then everything goes black.

End chapter.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
((**14.5**))

Voreverl is in the void.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl takes a moment to take in her lack of surroundings "Oh... Here again. Better than a sinking ship, I guess." She takes a seat and just waits.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: The guy with the sunglasses from last time runs over from just outside her vision. "YOU! The one from before...! I knew it couldn't have been a fluke..." ((Image attached so you remember.))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

attachments.url: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\artworks-Er7uhyvuiqiPqY0w-1xbwSw-t500x500-7DC16.jpg

messages.content: "Oh, hey, you stuck here too? Listen, I'm not really in the mood for a big evil speech. Just, uh... be intimidated by my invasion of your... home, I guess? For being such prominent villains, lawyers sure have no sense of interior design."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: He looks confused. "Lawyers? ...Ah, do you have some impression of who I am?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "What, you wearing that gaudy suit for pleasure?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: He looks at his outfit. "Well, I think formal attire is important in the right contexts."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Right..." She cracks her knuckles, and stands up "Okay, let's just get this over with. Are you a minion, or a hero? Or just plain unimportant?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "Hm. Well, I feel like I'd try to do the right thing most of the time. But so would everyone. That doesn't seem like a hero. I guess minion feels apt, in some abstract sense. Under the mechanisms of corporate hierarchy, perhaps all are minions. I don't know if I'm important. Do we know each other?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "...I want to say no, but I can't say for sure I wouldn't just forget someone as boring as you." She begins to walk in circles around him "Seriously, corporate hierarchy? You're still beholden to that crap? Have some fun, break some rules, let people know your name! Actually, no, don't do that. They need to keep room to remember my name. Which is Voreverl Leocot, by the way."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "I see. Hello, Voreverl. I'm pretty sure I was something with a J... Joe? Maybe."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "That's great, minion number 4... Or, well, I guess number 3 now..." She stops pacing "You didn't, uh, happen to see my... strategy meeting with Eric last time we met, did you?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "I don't know who that is, so no. I had just awoken here when I spotted someone nearby and walked towards you. That must've been.... I don't really know how long ago. I don't seem to have a watch."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "From the perspective of Voreverl Leocot, it's been a few days. I guess whatever assholes set up this place could have made time all weird and messed up, though. Lost four months of my life from this dimension hopping bullshit."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "I see. The Antarctica Project... I think."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: She glares at him "What, you involved in it? You know something, shades? You keeping some tactical advantage from me?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "I know nothing. I guess that must sound ridiculous - 'what? how couldn't he know anything?'. But it's pretty close to true. I guess I have some woefully cliche memory loss."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Convenient... for me, that is. Don't have to listen to your life story or whatever. Yes, you'll make a fine minion. A blank slate, no attachments to hold you back from throwing yourself into the heat of battle to protect your dark overlord. Not that I need any more, I'm in no short supply of loyal slaves."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "Haha, what?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Look, just swear loyalty to me. I can probably get you out of here if you do."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "I'm not sure what you're asking me to do."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Look, just..." She sighs "Fine, fine. I'm clearly not getting my point across like this." She takes a breath and puffs out her chest "Gweheheheh! Behold, the unsealed box of Pandora herself! The ten plagues of biblical proportion personified into human form! An evil unlike anything your pea-sized brain could possibly imagine! Bow before Voreverl Leocot, or die a miserable wretch who foolishly stood against the unstoppable march of her evil empire!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "I see.... Chūnibyō (中二病) (**Eighth-grader syndrome**). Okay. I wouldn't want to get in your way, certainly." He bows respectfully.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I could do without the armchair psychology, but you have the right idea." She takes out her PDA and thrusts it towards him "Haven't had much luck with this feature so far, to say the least, but no villain ever conquered out of fear. Uh, their own fear, that is. Whatever, point is, you won't be of use to me stuck here. Hold this."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: He holds it. "Hm. The design seems vaguely familiar... I would assume this was created by the same people I worked with."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: She furrows her brow "...So you are with them."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Maybe? You say ‘them’ rather disparagingly.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "The ones behind this joke of a project are my greatest enemy. Well, second behind Bernard Zie. Maybe third behind, uh, that blond chick... Whoever she was. I guess she was more just a representation of the universe ruining my life, though." She crosses her arms in thought "The order doesn't really matter. What does matter is whether or not I can use you as bait."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
“Bernard Zie… that’s…”

A monitor with a keyboard attached is now visible. The entire space is kind of vaguely defined, really, but ‘Joe’ appears to have developed an intuition about it, and walks up to the monitor.

“Yes, of course… I had largely dismissed it, but that’s the same name. A record related to Bernard Zie is stored here, for some reason.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "So, his filth found its way even in here. I'd normally not bother myself with records of a fool's utter failures. Well, maybe for a quick laugh. But gathering information on enemies is the greatest way to ensnare them in a devilishly clever trap by yours truly." She tries to see the monitor over Joe's shoulder "Anything I can use against him? Easy target relatives? Fears? A love of cheese that I can exploit with a human sized mouse trap?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “*Otokonoko (男の娘)…*” He mutters, scrolling through #deleted-channel. “I don’t really know. He seems quite resilient in his own way. What exactly do you have against him? Is it because he’s gay?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "...No. What? No. Homosexuality is one of the greatest crimes you can commit in modern society. Were anyone else to do it, I'd hold a deep respect for them. He's just making a mockery of it. That bastard stole my life. Both my original body in Arctica, and my superior body on Earth. He... he tried to erase the existence of Voreverl Leocot! That cannot stand!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
“Your body…? Hm. I guess such a thing… would be possible. It’s all data, abstracted enough…” he murmurs to himself, somehow closing the text stream and opening up what looks to be Microsoft Excel. You have no fucking idea what he’s doing in Microsoft Excel. 

“…Just… just checking. For the sake of posterity. What year is it, to your knowledge?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "2022, last time I checked. Well, 917 in Arctica. Gweheh, those fools are so behind us, I almost feel bad for them. 'Almost' being the key word, of course."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “I see. Well, I don’t really know what date system is used in Arctica. Or that there was one. 917 sounds exceptionally silly and devoid of meaning to me. But the other is as I fear. I’ll trust you, given I have no other choice. The mention of year in that document made me certain… it should be 1997.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "You've been stuck here for 25 years...? Well, your life isn't as important as mine, so my loss of four months is still the greater tragic backstory. Regardless, I suppose it's nice to have some company in the department of lives ruined by this project. What do you say, wanna help me tear it down? Get your revenge?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “I don’t feel confident in such a bold motive, but I’m certainly willing to assist you. Haven’t been granted much else to do.” He holds out your PDA. “Do you want this back?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: She stares at it for a few seconds before snatching it back "I was hoping that'd do something. Lost my last transferable minion, and with you stuck here, you won't exactly be of much use to me... Or, at least, I thought not. That computer do anything other than talk about Bernard Zie and tell you the year?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “It— well, it has a lot of data visualization software. Really impressive stuff. I believe there should be more information accessible along the lines of that Bernard record, but the navigation is incredibly unintuitive. It also isn’t exactly very promising as a source of information. It reads like an amateur creative writing project.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Fools wasting their lives away writing, instead of making their dreams into a reality... That's what separates me from the riffraff. So, these records are all just fiction, then? Someone just couldn't get enough of a real Bernard Zie, they had to make a fake one too?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “They’re presented as if they’re real, at least. An embellished retelling. I don’t exactly have the means to verify if this really happened. Or ‘really happened’ in the sense that this would be able to.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Anything about... *me* in there?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “No mention of a ‘Voreverl’, no. I’d remember that name.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "...Hardly a record worth keeping, then. Whatever, useless garbage, how unexpected." She looks around "Anything else in this place? Got a TV and couch to pass the time?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Not… that I’m aware of. Though there’s still a lot I don’t know. I witnessed something very peculiar the other… well, I’m inclined to say ‘day’, but I don’t know.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Peculiar, huh? Alright then, lay it on me, minion. Got nothing else to do until I get randomly zapped back to... I want to say Earth, but honestly who knows. My existence is a force of chaos, probably threw a wrench into the mastermind's plans just by being here."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “It’s hard to describe, but… I saw a structure of some sort far away. I tried to investigate, but couldn’t seem to get any closer. I could see inside it, too. It’s like… in computer graphics, textures are one-sided by default. So you can look through any wall you stand behind if you exit a building perhaps you were meant to stay inside.” He thinks about trying to explain that again, but doesn’t. “There might have been something in there. Alive.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Wow, a structure with see-through walls, this place is getting more exciting by the second. Congratulations developers of The Antarctica Project, you invented glass." She rolls her eyes "Whatever, it sounds like a more interesting evil lair than quite literally nothing. Take me there."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “It’s not here anymore. At least, I can’t see it. I could attempt to recreate it, though.” With unusual familiarity with keyboard shortcuts, and without waiting for confirmation, he opens and utilizes an application for sketching floor-plans. The rough outline he ends up creating is a perfect dodecagon, with 6 doors positioned equally blah blah blah you get the gist. That fucking layout.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Hm... Not the worst evil lair I've seen. What, does each door lead to a gauntlet for the heroes to overcome and unlock passage to the villain's throne room? Oh, and they could get picked off one by one until it's just the chosen hero... Yeah, that'd be good, real good." She nods to herself.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “It intrigues me that they chose twelve sides. I very particularly remember that.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Really? That's what intrigues you? Holy shit, if they let you loose, you could get a higher kill count than me from just boring victims to death. Is this what you do to pass the time? Just count walls?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
“I think there really are twelve walls. It, as an attribute, wins by default in intrigue against your scenario, which did not happen.”
He scratches his head. “Well, maybe it did. I wasn’t close enough to discern what was going on there.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "You're probably right, no one would be genius enough to think of such a dastardly use of an evil lair before I did. That's what makes me the greatest villain of all time. Unlike you, the greatest wall-counter of all time. Congratulations on your title, you earned it."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “I would assume that title would require a quantity much higher than twelve, actually.” ((🤓))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

inlineEmojis.name: 🤓
inlineEmojis.imageUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\1f913-67AB1.svg

messages.content: "Hmph, I don't need sass from a minion. Know your place, and accept the praise of Voreverl Leocot gratefully."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Voreverl… it just ticks me off! Don’t like the name, sorry. Nothing against you. But jeez. Something about that.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Nothing... against me? Oh, that's real interesting... I thought for sure you would have some kind of reason for insulting my very existence. Or are you just too stupid to realize what kind of enemy you can make with talk like that. Huh? What is it!?" She gets all up in his face.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “You’re somewhat unpleasant, I guess. But not enough to be unbearable. I wonder. Were you that surprised by my attire because you’ve never held an actual job before?” He asks this calmly.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I... I'm the *only* person to hold an actual job! I rule the world! I destroy civilizations! Gweheheh, whatever you did, it has nothing on me! You're the fake! Just, just... dressing how you're supposed to... doing what you're told... it's disgusting!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Oh, which ones? The civilization of your own credit score?” He chuckles adultly. “Look, I’d honestly have guessed you were from the fantasy world, not earth. This won’t do you any favors in the latter.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "That attitude is why your life will amount to nothing. Oh, Joe, you need to wear a suit and tie. Oh, Joe, you need to work at The Antarctica Project. Oh, Joe, you need to stand in this void for 25 years. You're just... just a nobody! No one will remember you! But they'll remember me. I don't need a credit score. I don't need to work at a zoo. I'll reinvent society, just wait."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “It definitely hasn’t been 25 years.” He mutters.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "...Yeah, you look pretty human. I don't know how it works for those Arctican creatures, but even a villain as resilient as me couldn't survive in this place that long. Is there even any cereal, or, like, water here?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Hm. No, I haven’t seen any. Curious. I wonder if that will become a problem.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I'll see if I can bring some to you next time. Assuming I actually get out of here. It's never taken this long before. Gweheheh, might have to break my way out at this rate."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “I would be interested to see such a thing, were it possible.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: ((Session fcuking end))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “I don’t think it’s possible, though.” He muses.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl crosses her arms, annoyed "Clearly you still don't understand who you're dealing with here. This place is no different from prison, and if modern security can't hold Voreverl Leocot, then this dinky little Antarctica Project doesn't stand a chance."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “There are no bars or restraints.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Just what I'd expect to hear from an unimaginative, boring office worker. Your life is the constraint! You just... accept the slop fed to you. I'm different. I broke out of Jane's prison, and I'll break out of Bern's too, so just watch me break out of this one. I'll make the criminal justice system into nothing more than my own personal revolving door!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Jane…” He mutters the name back to himself, and keeps typing up a storm on the inexplicable void terminal. “I just don’t think those skills are transferable, regardless of the possibility of escape.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I guess not. That's why I don't throw all my eggs at one house. I'm not some one-off gimmick villain, I'm the real deal. Adaptability, that's how you stay societally relevant. I won't be left behind just because the stage for my tyranny has changed."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Oh. Something new… hm.” A video feed is displayed.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl turns her attention to the monitor.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: It looks like the facility where Voreverl confronted John Leiblich. The feed buffers and slowly rises in quality.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "...What? Is this... Gweheheh, maybe this rest stop won't be a total waste of my valuable and important time. I don't suppose there's a remote detonation feature anywhere on this program? Maybe something to vent in toxic gas?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
It shows the last minute or so of the confrontation as Voreverl remembers it.

“Where… I know this guy. I’m certain I do.” The man in the void mumbles.

It reaches the end of Voreverl’s involvement, as she leaves in the direction of Eric Zeety.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I can't say you keep particularly good company. That pathetic fool is John Leiblich, a two-bit pesky fly who fancies himself a full fledged villain. This footage is from when I completely beat him in a battle of wits and guile, leaving his plans and mental state in ruins, so they can better match his marriage."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “John Leiblich…. John Leiblich. ……John Leiblich. No, that can’t be right.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "...Why not? That's his name. If anyone knows the name of John Leiblich, trust me, I'm the person. I've spent my life loathing that name of his."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
“No! This is not John Leiblich!” He holds his head.

The two women that Voreverl may or may not know as Joliene Swansong and Zita Praxis continue their standoff with Leiblich.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "That's a great objection you got there. Come back to me when you have a theory of your own. Or don't, I don't really care. I know I'm right, after all. Although, seeing you squirm in confusion would be a decent way to pass the time."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
The two women, both armed, corner John Leiblich. He stammers through negotiations and frees the two people he had imprisoned after failing to call his unconscious guards.

“How can you even say that for certain?! You probably just made some mistake!” Computer man cares way too much about this issue.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl starts to tune him out and stares at the monitor with a stupid smirk "Gweheheheh... Let him off too easy, honestly... Huh? Oh, you still on about this?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
The feed fast forwards through Joliene literally just reading a book and nothing else happening for a substantial amount of time.

“Why can’t I remember? I shouldn’t even need to be struggling to do that, how could I forget!”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "You forgot because it isn't important. I told you, this guy's a chump, a complete and utter waste of time. It's honestly a shame I haven't forgotten who he is. In fact, I'll probably do that once I completely crush him underneath my heel."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
Joliene mentions something about dungeons and dragons that upsets the man more.

As a shouting match over some nonsense about a guy named Detlef ensues on the feed, computer man continues to be agitated. “No, you’re wrong! He’s important!”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl gives the computer man a look of disgust "Said no one with a single brain cell ever. He's a footnote in my backstory. He probably won't even be explicitly named in chapters on my rise in history textbooks. You have picked the most pathetic possible molehill to die on."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
Computer man grunts in annoyance at her, but otherwise ignores Voreverl. He stares at the display, straining to understand… something.

On the screen, John has been pummeled twice by the furious queen.

"Fuck! Come on, I'm-- he's fine! I don't have direct control over all these mechanisms, but they're tested and safe! I don't like the guy, but that project head understands how to... run this sorta thing." John Leiblich pants desperately.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
Joliene exasperatedly steps between the two.
"Zita, you're—Look, I understand that you're frustrated, but this is a futile effort." She stabs John in the neck without even turning to face him. "I'm going to have to stop this here. You're just going to give yourself a migraine. I have it in good faith that he has no useful info for us. We must move on." Joliene removes the blade. John Leiblich collapses and bleeds out on the ground.

“WHAT?” Computer man screams reactively. “WHAT THE FUCK IS THAT?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "..." The blood drains from Voreverl's face, and she takes a step back "That... that... that's great... it... I wanted... gweh... I... urgh..." Voreverl's stomach begins to churn, and with a completely blank mind, she is unable to stop herself from falling to her knees and puking.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: The vomit pools and dissipates in the nothing. ((What a description.))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: The other man seems to pass out.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "What... what the fuck is wrong with him... dying before I killed him... I..." Tears well up in her eyes "I WASN'T DONE WITH HIM YET! He... He... THIS ISN'T HOW MY BACKSTORY GOES!!!" Voreverl gathers all of her strength to lift herself up and thrust herself forward towards the computer, attempting to punch through the monitor without even thinking.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: ((Roll strength.))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: It shatters.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "...No! Fuck! What happens next!? Where did they go!? Uh, uh..." She turns to the computer man, and kicks him in the side "Wake up! Fix this!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
The computer man doesn’t wake up. 

But someone else shows up. It’s difficult to see… the person appears almost pure black against a background which is also that. But there’s a clear humanoid presence.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: ”He can’t fix this. Nothing really broke, anyway. Not physically.”

author.name: johnantarctica

roles.name: if women are oppressed then why

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\27b199d830ef072abef78e3da451c51e-72E77.png

messages.content: "Fuck... Fuck! I should have been there! I should have... I wasn't done yet! I wasn't done! He... I still had plans! I still had plans! Dying to another low-rate... That asshole! Does he think dying can make up for everything! He deserves so much worse... I could have done worse! I should have!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
I maneuver towards shards of what once was a video feed, suspended in the air. I grab hold of one.
“Would that have helped? Would you have been satisfied?”

author.name: johnantarctica

roles.name: if women are oppressed then why

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\27b199d830ef072abef78e3da451c51e-72E77.png

messages.content: "Y-yeah! Obviously! I... I needed my revenge! I didn't get it from him yet... I just... I just needed more time! He... He ruined my life! How can I be fine with his ending like that!? How!? How is this happening!?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Because of the greatest waste of time ever conceived. The Antarctica Project. He died for none of his real sins or actions, but for interfering with something so trivial. And through the incompetence of two women in particular, on a smaller scale.”

author.name: johnantarctica

roles.name: if women are oppressed then why

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\27b199d830ef072abef78e3da451c51e-72E77.png

messages.content: "That's... that's right..." She balls up her fists "This project... This... This fucking circus show! That's my enemy! That's why I was put in that body! That's why I went through all of this... Why Eric... Ugh!" She stomps in anger "How do I kill it? Pulverize it! Destroy this fucking tumor on my perfect scheme!?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: ”I cannot provide you everything. After all, you shouldnt even have a real reason to trust me. But I can provide one guarantee, and one spot of hope.”

author.name: johnantarctica

roles.name: if women are oppressed then why

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\27b199d830ef072abef78e3da451c51e-72E77.png

messages.content: "You..." Voreverl finally begins centering some of her attention on the presence speaking to her "Who... Gweheh... It doesn't matter... Nobody important, I'm sure..."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: ”Not particularly, no. I have no real name. Perhaps you can call me Autumn. Though you should have no need to refer to me. The spot of hope is this: The consciousness of that man should not be fully lost. In the same way Strider over here can exist, it may be possible for me to retrieve his essence.” I gesture to the sunglasses man, since Voreverl probably wouldn’t get who I’m referring to.

author.name: johnantarctica

roles.name: if women are oppressed then why

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\27b199d830ef072abef78e3da451c51e-72E77.png

messages.content: "That... Gweh... Gwehahahahah! So... the afterlife is real now!? What, am I going to hell? Super hell? Sure, why not! Get him back in here! He isn't done suffering yet! I'm not... I can't be done yet!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: ”It is sort of like hell. …The more confident guarantee is chances for retribution against most other relevant figures. You will meet TGP and PH. You will overcome impossibility to meet Bernard Zie. You’ll become an incredible despot. …And you’ll meet the two who killed your father. Whatever conflicted feelings you have on them is your business. But me personally, I’m rooting against them.”

author.name: johnantarctica

roles.name: if women are oppressed then why

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\27b199d830ef072abef78e3da451c51e-72E77.png

messages.content: I crush the shard of an image within my hands, hoping that looks cool.

author.name: johnantarctica

roles.name: if women are oppressed then why

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\27b199d830ef072abef78e3da451c51e-72E77.png

messages.content: I look up. “What the fuck is he doing? Oh, god dammit.”

author.name: johnantarctica

roles.name: if women are oppressed then why

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\27b199d830ef072abef78e3da451c51e-72E77.png

messages.content: "...Don't tell me what I'm going to do. The universe is against me! Society too! If I get my revenge on this project... On whoever else is in my way... It will be because of my own effort! I'm going to do it because I want to, not because you told me to! Don't tell me shit I already know! Of course I'll be incredible, I'm Voreverl Leocot!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
”Oh, absolutely. I don’t actually ‘do’ anything.”

I leave.

author.name: johnantarctica

roles.name: if women are oppressed then why

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\27b199d830ef072abef78e3da451c51e-72E77.png

messages.content:
Voreverl can barely even parse being left alone before she ceases to be in this space.

((End session. End 14.5.))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl awakens… somewhere. Some vaguely suburban neighborhood, on a bench.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl takes a moment to adjust to the suddenness of the scenery change, especially after the recent rush of emotions and revelations. She clenches her hands a few times, feeling the sensation of returning to her body after the unusually long time away. After getting her bearings, she sits up straight on the bench and scans the area for life.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
There’s two people standing around on the sidewalk. One of them looks at you briefly.

Voreverl’s cellphone rings.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: With a reaction speed notably slower than that which would serve to protect an evil empire, Voreverl reaches to grab her phone and check the number.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: It’s Meryl.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
Voreverl's head feels just about ready to burst open, her grip on her phone just barely enough to keep from dropping it. She takes a deep breath, and slaps herself across the face as hard as she can. At the top of her lungs, she releases a declaration.

"I AM VOREVERL LEOCOT! I SHALL HAVE MY REVENGE! ALL WHO OPPOSE ME SHALL FALL! GWEHAHAHAHAH!" She answers the phone immediately after finishing this battle cry "Ms. Leiblich, it's been a while. For what reason do you interrupt my machinations? Spit it out!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: A sigh can be heard on the other end. "*Why am I so....* Yes, hello. It's you. I guess he got the timing right. I don't need this to be a drawn out thing, just a yes or no answer."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl takes a moment to respond, having to force the words up and out of her throat "...No! That's... I am ordering you to stay on the line for longer! I... am in need of information! You shall be a valuable non-renewable resource, with which I shall pollute the hopes of my ignorance that my enemies hold!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "The next transfer is the last one. You'll go to Arctica, whatever nonsense happens there will happen, and then you'll come back. And the project will be over. There's your info. I don't have the ability to stop it, but it won't be very long regardless."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "That... Indeed! My sheer intimidation was enough to torture what I needed out of you! You are quite crafty to know to avoid a confrontation with the likes of Voreverl Leocot!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
"Unfortunately not. It should be over by two weeks from now, is the point. I..."

She pauses. "...Do you know? About your father..."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl does not respond, not a single word comes to mind for her to even blurt out. Her breathing begins to speed up, coming in uneven clumps rather than a steady pace.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "...Sorry." Meryl Leiblich does not come up with any other words to say.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: It's a struggle to speak at this point, but Voreverl gathers up enough strength to manage "...Why are you apologizing? This is great news... My enemy is... I'm happy about this! Why wouldn't I be!? He's not even my father! I have no father! Good riddance, you bastard!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
The other end is silent for a few seconds before some undiscernible non-word noises. Crying... or laughter.
"Yes, so it goes... only I seem to remember anything... that's funny. Uuu. I agonized over what to do, but believed I'd regret it if I didn't even attempt to reach out about the funeral. Just to hear the 'no' myself. If you showed up, though, you'd just make a scene, wouldn't you? Maybe that's only right. You two deserve each other. I'm sure eeevveryone's satisfied with this outcome, then. *I'm not!*"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "..." Voreverl slowly begins to stand up, and upon completion, she starts pacing back and forth in front of the bench, taking in a deep breath before responding "...I could infiltrate the funeral. If it's for reconnaissance, Voreverl Leocot wouldn't need to make a scene."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "Yeah, yeah, that's fine. It's all fine if the result is okay. Right? I've been able to keep myself going with that for years. Talk is talk. It shouldn't matter what people present as, it's the modern world, takes all kinds. I mean, what do I care? What's the worst that could happen? You pull some insane stunt at an event to solemnly honor the memory of a dead man, he certainly won't be around to mind. What's it to me? Hey, did you know I don't have anything left but you? It's true! I gave up my career to start a family. I'd do it again! I don't regret choosing to be a human over a researcher! My social circle dissolved entirely when I became the mother of an international criminal, but I know that was just testing me, right? You need to hold onto what's most important as tight as you can, right? So it's okay. This is why we have faith. Because we need some way to believe things will work out, even when logic can't bring us there. There's a lot of things that are important that we only achieve through belief."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Mom, I..." Voreverl moves her hand to slap herself once again, but stops short, and just stands there for a moment. Tears begins to well before she can say anything "...I'm sorry... I'm sorry! I'm sorry! I'm sorry! It's all my fault! I... I left him alone with them! I could have stopped them! Voreverl Leocot could have! But... but now he's... and I can never take it back! I can't take any of it back!" Her eyes have stopped acting as wells for the tears, and instead serve as a hose for them to pour out of. Her nose does much the same. If Meryl could see her, Voreverl would appear as nothing but a disheveled mess.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: She trips over her own words, desperate to say something yet unable to grasp what it is. “Wh… um, oh, I… no, no it isn’t! There… I don’t even understand it yet, but he knew he was heading down a dangerous road. You were just trying to get by in a world he was tearing apart! And I knew… I knew him, what his problem was. I should have done something. I don’t know. I hate— th-that the last thing I said to him was about divorce. I don’t think I could’ve gone through with it. I just wanted to scare him. I thought…! I thought I could be the one to bring him to his senses. If I had called him out sooner, I might… Maybe… someone does need to be the bad guy sometimes.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "No... No!" She shakes her head furiously "You're just a minion, you couldn't do anything! He wouldn't listen to someone like you! This was between important people... real villains! I had the manpower... I could have had an army! I could have stormed that fucking pizzeria and stopped everything! But I screwed it up! I lost it! I killed dad just like I killed Eric!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “We’re only human…” She mutters, vaguely confused.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I'm... I'm not! Voreverl Leocot is a god! And... and Jane Leiblich is just... just an Arctican... I'm not even real, am I? I've just been playing pretend my whole life! You should have just let me die! At least then I'd be living as myself and not *this*!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “No! No. I refuse. I’m not going to play coy, or see if it’s a phase, or throw my hands in the air and wait. This is where I stand for something. If there was ever a good decision I’ve made in my life, it was that one. I don’t know if… he was your father or not. It’s a messy ordeal. But you’re my daughter. Whoever or whatever you are. I don’t care if you came from magic, or some machine, or some alien planet. It doesn’t matter at all.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
Voreverl falls to her knees and begins sobbing uncontrollably. Through the cries and wails of all her pent up emotional baggage coming to the surface at once, sounds vaguely resembling two words can be made out.

"...thank... you..."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “I’ll… call you back later. I need to, um, check some… things…”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: She hangs up.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl drops her phone and just holds her head in her hands, continuing to release screams and cries until she runs out of breath and feels her throat begin to tear.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: Someone approaches her, standing silently in front of Voreverl Leocot. It’s one of the two people she originally saw standing around.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl Leocot, without a second thought, springs to her feet. Even if there weren't tears in her eyes, she would not take a moment to check who this person is. Before she can even realize what she's doing, she tightly embraces them.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: They freeze up, startled, then half-return the gesture, patting her on the back.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: After a few seconds, Voreverl realizes what she's doing, and breaks it off. She tries to sputter something out, and after a couple attempts, ends up with a "...S-sorry..."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “It’s fine. There’s been much weirder.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl wipes her face off with her sleeve to try to appear a bit more presentable "...Weird? Gwehah! As if I'd be concerned with that! You and your puny mind have fallen hook, line, and sinker for my textbook manipulation tactics! Witness the power of Voreverl Leocot's deception!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Do you think it will work? I personally think that method of obfuscating true motivations is a bit overplayed. Unless you’re able to forge compelling evidence that you were actually acting with ulterior motive, it’s hard to believe that people believe it.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: She crosses her arms and looks away "A wise guy, huh? I'll have you know that I've successfully pushed away everyone in my life by informing them of my evil intentions! It's natural instinct to run in the opposite direction of a being of pure malice!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “It sounds as if you are terrible at manipulation, then.” They smile.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "That's... Voreverl Leocot is amazing at manipulation! The only reason you think that I'm not is that I'm tricking you into underestimating me! So just... leave me alone. You're not even worth considering wasting my time on, considering how easy it was to play you right into my hand."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Are you certain you want to be alone?” The person’s expression takes on a variety of forms very quickly. “I think you are not capable of existing in isolation.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Not capable!? I'm... I'm capable of anything!" She points an accusatory finger "You're the one who's incapable of understanding my machinations! So just forget what you saw here! Keep your head down and your mouth shut about what you saw me doing, got it? This is a threat!"

author.name: natyobb

I wouldn’t put it like that.
“Anyway, I’m not going to pretend you’ll be guaranteed fine. At least one of the clusterfuck of people in there might want to kick your ass. I just think it would be inconsistent for you to shrink away with that knowledge.”

messages.content:
“What the hell is this?! Are you trying to humiliate me?” The boy yells at his mother.

“Uhm, I just… I mean, this is something you like, right? I thought it would be a… just a kind gesture, since I happened to meet…” Jane sheepishly speaks in her defense.

The boy holds his head. “I haven’t… my interests, it’s been months since I was remotely into — even if I still was, what would make you think this was a good idea?”

“I’m sor… um…” Jane sighs.

Dawn is enthralled by this, completely ignoring Voreverl. They have become the opposite of done.

“I don’t want to scheme anything! I just want to be left alone…!” He pouts.

“You know I can’t do that.” Jane speaks softly.

“You still display an axebroom on your wall, kid. I know what you are, dork.” Dawn chuckles. The child puts his hand on his head, mortified. 

“Who the fuck is this, even?!” He switches the topic to Voreverl.

author.name: scipe

messages.content: "An axe, huh? This kid's got a violent side, I like it." She places down the bag of chips to gesture with both hands while speaking "Listen well, child, because I will only introduce myself to you this one time. My machinations are far too grand to waste any longer on you. I am the bringer of death to this world! The rat that carries the plague! The Jenga piece that is just a bit too tightly packed! To cross swords with me in battle is to witness your future crumble like dust in the wind! Do you know why!? It is because I am Voreverl Leocot, the very manifestation of evil itself! Bask in the terror radiating off of me, and pray your unimportant shell of a life never crosses paths with mine again!"
