messages.content: “Oh. From the pope thing? I thought you were in jail.” Thank god this guy keeps up on all the silliest and zaniest news around.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl freezes in place "Y-you... You actually..." She proceeds to run up to the kid and get all up in his face "You've heard of me! I mean... of course you have, I'm Voreverl Leocot! I'm... everyone fears my name! Gwehahah! I've won! People know about me, they're afraid of me! Suck it, John! You're twenty feet under the ground, and I'm flying through the stratosphere! Eclipsing the sun itself with a pure mass of evil! Look at me now!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
“My name is not John.” He doesn’t know what else to say.

Dawn is deep in thought.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Don't you see what this means, minion?" Voreverl Leocot jumps onto a chair or table or something, whatever furniture is around "I've never met this kid before... He doesn't know anyone I know, completely unrelated from me! If my evil can permeate through the news like some kind of corrosive memetic force and trickle down to him, just a random nobody... I can do anything! I've won against this... universal force, keeping me down! No matter what I do, it keeps suppressing me, but now... there's no coincidence this is happening now! After I've been unchained from my past, and found a hero to torment! I've become too powerful for anyone to stop me!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
“But, you’re Bruumcordkitten, right? Just assumed you’d be… hmph.” Dawn takes an educated guess.

The boy’s face takes on several exciting different shades, as he freezes in place.

“Also, I thought she was female.”

This causes him to flee back upstairs.

Dawn pouts. “Damn. Pushed too hard. Oh well.” What an exciting diversion!

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl crosses her arms "Ahem, *minion*. I believe celebrations are in order for Voreverl Leocot's conquest of the collective consciousness."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
“Haha, like from… anyway, yeah, that’s just a coincidence. I suppose the kid does know you independently of anything. Congratulations.”

Jane is on the verge of tears. This really isn’t about her. “What just… you… what was that?!”

“Your son presents as a woman online in a deeply homophobic country. Read into that whatever you want. I did what you asked! Let’s leave, Voreverl.” Dawn.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Finally!" Voreverl gets down and pats Jane on the shoulder "Don't worry, your kid's a real standout gal! Studied up on her history properly. I see myself in her a bit... that's how you know she'll come out well." She leaves the house.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
Jane is unresponsive.

Dawn follows Voreverl. “Ah. Anyway, what now?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Excellent question minion, to which I have an even better answer. To find Haruka Tanaka, we need to learn two important pieces of information. First, where she is, and second, where we are."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “We’re in Tunisia. Did you not know that? Sorry, I guess I forgot how up to speed you are.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “That family has really good English. Wonder why.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Gweheheheh... We're halfway to completing our goal already. Haruka Tanaka... sounds Japanese. Let's start our search there. We'll comb the country for any trace of her!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “She *was* in Japan. No question about that. She lived there, not in secret or anything. I’m less sure she is now. I could hook you up with the detective in charge of her case, at least.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Ugh, working with the police?" Voreverl throws up her arms "Fine, fine! I will simply be taking advantage of them anyway! This is no different from the Pope."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Yeah. She’s a little… off, anyway. You have a phone, right?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl takes out her phone "I'm not stuck in the medieval ages just because I've been stuck in that pathetic world."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “You can never take anything for granted.” Dawn provides Voreverl with two numbers; one their own, the other an Inspector Kamala Kyros of Kyoto Prefecture.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: The unfortunate number of identical letters is a coincidence.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "They better know English... or Italian, I guess. The terror of Voreverl Leocot could never be properly translated through an interpreter." She calls the detective.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
**“これは誰ですか ?!”**
This hurts Voreverl’s ears a little from how loud it is, and is also obviously not a voice you recognize.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Gweh... Do not disrespect the ears of Voreverl Leocot with your made up pretend language! English is the chosen tongue of my empire, do you speak it?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Voreverl… that name.” Her English is decent. “Hmph. What is this…?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I'm told you're the lead detective on the case of Haruka Tanaka. I have business with her, so I am suggesting a truce between the forces of Voreverl Leocot and the police of your country. We shall pool together our resources and find her!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “How on Earth did you get this number? …I am willing to collaborate if you sell out your boss.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "My...? Listen, lady! Maybe you don't understand who you're talking to! Voreverl Leocot works for no one! I was supplied this number by my minion, and called of my own volition! Got it!?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “I see. Is that how it is? This would be nonsensical if you truly were in the same allegiance as Rikarasu… I have nothing to lose. Fine. I’ll believe you. But who is this ‘minion’?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Nobody important. Dawn... something. They're a writer, apparently."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Hm. I suppose it is likely possible to track me down if someone is motivated. What interest do you have in that woman? I can provide information, at the least.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Well, Ms. Piggie, I'm conducting something of an investigation myself. I don't give a rat's ass about Haruka or her crimes, she sounds like a real small-time villain, but my only lead says she knows something important to me."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “This does not help at all. Okay.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I don't want to confuse your pea-sized brain with all the details. Listen, you mentioned Rikarasu, right? She ever mention The Antarctica Project? Whole big global conspiracy type deal, and Haruka was wrapped up in it."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “She mentioned you, at least. Are you a defector from this conspiracy?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Fuck no, I'm a victim of it! But that's neither here nor there, I'm not trying to sue them for damages or anything. Voreverl Leocot's revenge will be much more thorough... they'll regret everything they've done."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Heh. …Fine. I can’t very well moralize to you. The Kaihime case. That’s what it’s called. You’re obviously not Japanese, so I doubt you’re familiar; that’s a historical figure. Female warrior regarded as heroic. Probably like Joan of Arc, which I assume you’ve heard of. It never went anywhere, though. That information. Useless. Who knows why it was picked as the name behind the operation. She’s clearly not dumb enough to leave deliberate hints or anything.” She pauses for a moment. “It was mostly about selling crack.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Gweheheh, sounds like my kind of organization. Well, not really. I would have a much broader list of crimes to be hunted down for, my evil can hardly be contained by *just* selling crack. Still, for someone I've barely heard of, it's not bad."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “…You’re like some asinine reflection of her, god. The same guy with different words. Whatever. The point is, we tracked the operation down, but too late. Haruka Tanaka left the country with her son and has been missing since. There were two leads, so to speak…”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Well, come on, spit them out! You've done nothing but cross off a single country on our list of possible hiding spots for her lair! Hardly a time save so far, and I'm a very busy villain."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “I make no promise of results. You’re promising me nothing, after all. There were two relevant figures left behind when Haruka fled. One is Rikarasu Endo. The other is Kyle Groverfield. Both have gone by pseudonyms too asinine to humor. …Fainda Shinjitsu and Intuition Overdrive, just for full transparency. The former is simple. She operated a fradulent detective business at absurd rates in order to launder the money of the operation. Kyle is much more confusing. We could find very little out about him, but Haruka signed the legal rights to her home off to him before vanishing.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “Both were arrested, but… well, this is where your mention of a conspiracy seems much more credible.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Gwehoh? I'm listening. Your leads already intrigue me, continue doing well and perhaps I shall reward you with my knowledge of Intuition. I want to see the charges against him stick as much as anyone who's been in his unbearable presence would."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Both of them underwent symptoms of an inexplicably long period of unconsciousness… and at some point, escaped. I should be able to tell you more, right? I agree. Even with cameras disabled, the nature and timing of when they were, what was left in the cell… all of it should be pertinent information. Information we should *have*. But they keep… ugh. The harder I push on this, the more I suffer for it. They’ve demoted me to a parking ticket guy by this point. I’m only still in charge of the case because they’ve more-or-less closed it. More active offenders to focus on. What a load of shit. I bet they wish they could get rid of me. Kept as some fuckin’ diversity hire, probably.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "...I really don't care about your personal life. Either you fall in line as a faceless mook, or you make a name as a revolutionary. You tried to half-ass it, that's your fault. Anyway, that all you got?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “*Snrk*. Listen, kid. This supervillain shtick? It isn’t cute. Nobody’s gonna fall for you, and you certainly aren’t going to achieve whatever you’re going for. You stole the pope’s car, right? That’s where you peak. Some individual if surprising bit of mischief. Your best hope for anything more is leeching off the efforts of others who are pathetic and desperate enough. Like me, sure. I’m a failure. But my path wasn’t. Think on that, alright, brat? Aha… it’s gratifying to find a version of Rikarasu I can talk to.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Yeah, cool, whatever." Voreverl stopped listening halfway through. She hangs up and puts away the phone. "Well, that wasn't *un*helpful, minion. You're not completely dead weight."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Cool. I really don’t think Haruka matters, though. So this is probably useless. Her only relevance beyond the facts of Rikarasu’s situation is that Zaquera Culbasko had sex with her. Mean to say, but it’s true. That’s just my take, though.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl stares at Dawn with a mix of disgust and confusion "...Your perception of relevance is way off." Voreverl takes out her PDA and begins typing up some messages.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: She tosses the PDA to Dawn "Here, tell me if any new messages come in. If Haruka's going to be anywhere, it's not gonna be this backwater irrelevant blip on the map. Let's get to an airport."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “I think that’s exactly the kind of place it makes sense to hide, but alright!” Dawn smiles.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl checks her phone's map app to figure out where an airport is. "So you got, like, a car or something?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Not at the moment. Where do you plan to fly, anyway?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "No idea, just don't want to waste time getting there once more leads come in. Ugh, I sound like my boss. I mean, not my real boss... which I don't have one of! Just my zoo... boss." Voreverl looks at the ground "Well, I suppose it wouldn't hurt to make a stop in Italy, make sure my future flamingo minions are being groomed properly."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Well, alright. There *is* a faster way than air travel… but it might be risky. You’re not on any strict time limit right now, so the hour or so shouldn’t matter.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "...Minion, are you suggesting what I think you are? That sounds a lot like how Arcticans speak of teleportation magic. If magic is usable here on Earth, that would be *very* important to know."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “No, it’s not magic. Probably. But yes, teleportation. We’d need to be lucky enough to not run into one of the other guys who knows about this. I’ve kind of gained access illegitimately.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl clicks her tongue "To be a warlock in a world where magic isn't commonplace... it would have been perfect. Regardless, explain the process to me. Voreverl Leocot shall decide if the risk is worth it, that's not for you to worry about."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Oh, the only risk is if you give a shit about the Star Trek transporter problem. The process itself is fine. It’s just about not getting caught.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "The wh- No, no, I don't care! I shall survive whatever sci-fi mumbo jumbo nerd shit this is! Just tell me how to use it!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “If you want. We made it here that way, it should probably be fine.” Dawn leads the way, if Voreverl is willing to follow.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl goes in the same direction, which happens to result in her being behind Dawn.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: Fantastic. This entails entering a very stereotypical feeling secret passage in an alleyway, behind which is a series of tunnels. It is a long-but-not-too-long uneventful trip which concludes in a dodecagonal room that has six doors in it (including the one entered from).

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Hold on, something about this is..." Voreverl counts the walls "I knew it! This is the place! The one Joe saw! That stick-in-the-mud wasn't seeing things, after all!" She waves at a random wall "Hey! Void minion! Look at me! I got out, while you're still trapped in that eternal prison! Sucks to be you!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
“Who’s J—”
Dawn holds back from making a terrible mistake. “Well, there’s like fifty fucking thousand rooms that look identical to this. That’s an exaggeration, but still. Kind of the key to the mechanics of teleportation. Identical environments on both sides.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Oh. Still, doesn't hurt to mock the less fortunate, just in case they can hear you."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “An intriguing ideology.” Dawn takes a rock they brought in from outside and throws it at the ceiling. This causes a thud noise, followed by a computer terminal descending from the ceiling. “Italy, right?” Dawn confirms.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Yeah... that's right... Do you really have to throw something at it to get it to activate? Seems like a concussion hazard... What a genius design."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “I found this trick a while ago. I can also try to contact someone to enable this, but it’s easier to avoid that.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Yes, the less of a trail we leave, the larger of a betrayal it will be when they realize we've been using their system against them! What are you waiting for, minion? I command you to begin the teleportation of Voreverl Leocot!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Okay.” Dawn presses a small amount of buttons.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “We’re here.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: The room looks the same.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Hmph. Rooms need to look the same, yeah I get it, but still they could... I don't know, install some kind of light show in all the rooms? At least *try* to make it fun to use." Voreverl looks around "So, same door we came in, or...?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “This one should work.” Dawn heads through a door, stopping shortly after. “Hm.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl follows "What's the problem? Getting cold feet from approaching the nation most corrupted by my influence?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “I think someone knew we’d be coming.” Dawn picks up a small slip of paper from the floor. “…Interesting. It’s for you.” They hand this to Voreverl.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "The machinations of Voreverl Leocot could never be anticipated! They probably just left one at every location. Gweheheh... quite the evil waste of trees." Voreverl reads the slip of paper.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
> LEOCOT

> The roof. Now.

> Bring the PDA.

That’s all that was wrote.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Gweheheheh... Gwehahahahahahah! GWEHEHEHEHEHEH!" Voreverl rips the paper in half "A challenge, then!? Fool! An invitation of Voreverl Leocot is an invitation of the cruel mistress of death! To the roof, minion!" Voreverl runs ahead.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
Dawn pauses, examining something. Voreverl doesn’t know the way, so is gatekept for at least a second. “They left a flower with it, too. Why?” Dawn runs after Voreverl, holding a small bluish plant. “I thought it was left mistakenly for Bern, at first, because of that. Sort of his whole motif. Someone with a predisposition to the poetic, clearly. A mockery of a gesture of love. But you’re clearly named in the note.”

Dawn runs ahead of Voreverl, remembering well enough how to ascend the floors of this complex.

They don’t know. They as in both of them, probably, as well as the single person who is addressed with they, I guess.

It’s not about there being a flower. It’s which one.

In the language of flowers, it holds a variety of meanings across cultures, sometimes contradictorily. It symbolizes sorrow. It means hope. It represents humility and faith, sapphic love and warding away evil spirits. It could be for any of these reasons the flower was chosen. It could also be much simpler.


It’s a violet.

((End 15.))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl reaches the top of the stairs. Behind this door would seem to be the roof of this surprisingly tall complex. DA trails behind, breathing heavily. Your energy is unmatched.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl reaches a hand out to open the door, but pauses and examines Dawn "...Voreverl Leocot's death match of wits is about to occur. You don't seem to be... much for the physical. I haven't run out of use for you, yet, minion. Stay out of the way if I need to enact my evil judgement on this foolish challenger. Unless I tell you to get in the way, as a last resort."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Yeah, sure. Okay.” DA leans against the wall.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl, with her ducks in a row, all ready to march out and raze the lands before her, slams the door open.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: Violetta Esposito sits atop a currently inactive AC unit, looking at her phone with earbuds in. She spots Voreverl out of the edge of her vision, and takes the headphones off. She stares silently.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl quite literally trips over herself upon seeing this, involuntarily having pulled back from her sprint out the door. She pushes away the pain of falling on her ass, and spits out the first thing she can to keep control of the situation "I... I'm stronger now! Don't try anything... I've got magic! I beat up a pirate... a sky pirate! She was really big, too!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Is that what you’ve been doing?” She rolls her eyes, and drops down from the AC thing.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "...Yeah!" She stumbles to her feet "Much cooler than whatever you've been up to, which is so irrelevant and unimportant that I haven't heard a thing about it! I would totally make fun of it otherwise, but you're clearly not worth my time."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: Violetta drags a large cardboard box out from behind the AC thing. “Yeah. Sure. You really haven’t done much on Earth, hm?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "That's not true at all! Voreverl Leocot never ceases her endless villainous revolution! I raided a government facility! I became the pope! My Rube Goldberg machine of machinations is going off without a hitch, so prepare to be caught in its jaws!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Who have you hurt?” Violetta stares at you.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl crosses her arms and smirks "No one survives an encounter with Voreverl Leocot unscathed! Not my father, rotting in his little shithole rat den, and certainly not those who distract me from my goals. You'll face your punishment in due time."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “No, you definitely didn’t kill him. Sorry to hear the news, by the way.” She smirks, but it seems incongruent with whatever her eyes are expressing.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "...I got some good licks in. Plus, I may as well have killed him, I left him to be consumed by the rabid dogs of the monarchy. He could only have survived with my supervision. It's like... y'know..." She motions with her hand as she thinks "Like a Bond villain. I left him in my trap! The main villain doesn't dirty her hands with background characters."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “That’s good. Good.” Violetta nods to herself. “That you think that. Real outstanding gymnastics. This would’ve been pointless if you’d already gained any sense.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I have no need for sense... other than the sixth sense, the sense of evil! Gweheh... heh..." She quickly gives up on one of the most forced laughs she's ever given "Just get to the point. You don't call someone to a rooftop to just catch up. Are we dueling, or what?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Sure. Yeah. Sure.” She steps away from the box, moving closer to the edge of the building. “I always knew you were a rich brat, Jane, but it seems at every turn I find you get coddled even more than I thought.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "What are you even talking about!? I... I disowned my family! My father wanted me dead! I live in a shitty apartment... by choice! The point is they didn't buy me a place to live, or anything, okay!? I'm a self built villain!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “I don’t really care about how much you want to larp as a commoner.” Violetta holds up her phone, staring at it. “While you were busy being deluded into being a pirate, I followed a trail that honestly? It was probably meant for you. And I solved it. Everything. The whole big mystery behind all this horseshit.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Oh, congrats, you're such a big girl for figuring that out. I had no need to follow a trail set out for me, since Voreverl Leocot breaks the trails! She runs straight through the woods! I know everything about The Antarctica Project! Everything relevant anyway. I've got the hit list of who needs to pay."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “That’s nice. But you’re wrong. There was only one hiccup recently. Otherwise you’ve been following along someone else’s design perfectly.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl shrugs "Everyone likes to take credit for how things turn out. Play pretend mastermind, say they had it all planned the whole time. Let's not kid ourselves, Voreverl Leocot is an unpredictable force of chaos! Schrodinger's cat remains within my box! My decisions are unobservable, and poisonous to those who cross me!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
“If you were playing the game fair, I wouldn’t be the only one pushing back against your nonsense. …Still, I was taken for a fool myself for a while there.”
Violetta walks over to you. “Do you have the PDA?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: She smirks "It's around. Tell me why you want it, and I might let you have a look. We can always do the interrogation the hard way, of course, but wasted time is evil deeds unperformed, so I'd prefer to avoid things getting ugly."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “There’s a lot of things I want to tell you so we can settle this feud at last. But I don’t think you’ll just believe all the things I have to say without proof. So I’ll give it. By showing I really do know things about this project, starting with the secret of that little thing.” She holds out a hand expectantly. “Have you ever heard of a man named *Rupert Darke*?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Settle the feud... so you wish to apply for a position as my underling? Gweheheh, very well, I'll listen to your expository groveling." She snaps her fingers "Minion, the PDA!" She holds out a hand towards the doorway to the stairs.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
“Oh. Okay. Right.” DA seems to have forgotten they even had it. They scurry over and place it into Violetta’s hand. Violetta kicks DA and runs away.

“Thanks.” She holds her phone and the PDA in one hand, and tosses both up into the air. Light shimmers off the screen… and then both plummet down over the edge of the building onto ground level.
“Now we’re alone.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl rushes over to the edge of the roof "You... shitty little... I need that! You might not have enough friends to need a communication device, but my network of minions are my only lead!" She desperately scans the ground for her PDA.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “I’ll fuckin’ get it.” DA, voice notably less enthused than before, gets to their feet and walks back over to the stairwell. “You two can hash out whatever insane thing this is yourselves.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl glares at Violetta "Great secret, never knew objects could be thrown! My war plans have been completely overturned by this revolutionary technique! Truly, I am thrilled to see what trick you think of next."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: She mutters obscenities. “I’ve freed us both. From here on out… no one can interfere.” She looks at the sky. “Not even you.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I don't give a shit about this... what even is this? Some kind of skin deep philosophical garbage? Technology was the real villain all along! Except no, it wasn't, it was just a tool for me! I can still throw you off this roof, how's that for interfering, huh!? Wanna test your luck that you're as sturdy as that PDA?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “I’d love to. I’d love you to have anything to provide that isn’t meaningless bullshit. But I’m not holding out hope.” She takes a deep breath.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I don't 'provide'. I take away from others. I burn down societies, tear it apart at the seams, and leave nothing left! You sure aren't giving me anything valuable here. Is that gonna change, or do you really want to see the power of Voreverl Leocot firsthand?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "I could start with the 'amazing endgame twist' you were probably going to get eventually. Hope you're not too weak to handle it." She looks to the side, annoyed.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Sure, go ahead, dazzle me with your all-seeing eye of time-wasting. I've got nothing better to do while my minion finishes their job. Might as well demonstrate my indomitable will to the masses who don't know their place."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: She stares ahead at nothing in particular. "None of it's real, Jane. It's all a farce."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl's hands tighten into fists "The only farce here is your understanding of who you're talking to! ...Ugh, whatever! I know Arctica is a simulation or something, okay!? That was like months ago! ...In your time, at least."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "No. This." She gestures around. "They made us. Something like that. Big whoop." Violetta shrugs. "It's not like it actually matters to anyone."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
Voreverl stares at Violetta, taking in the words. Something almost comes out of her mouth several times, but instead she just looks around her, taking in the view. Eventually, it's too much to bear, and the floodgates open. "Gw...

GWEHEHEHEHEHEHEHEHEHEH! GWEHAHAHAH! GWEHHHHAAHAHAAAAA!" She lowers herself onto the rooftop and begins holding her stomach, kicking her legs, and quite literally rolling around laughing. "I am *such* a dumbass!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "Yeah."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: She calms down a bit, and just lays still, arms out, staring at the sky, grinning ear to ear. "Ever since... Avdol told me where I came from. I was actually *worried* about not being real! Gwehah! Imagine that! Voreverl Leocot turning out to the least real person in the world! It's ridiculous! But now... the playing field's been evened out! ...I would have closed the gap anyway, of course."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "Voreverl Leocot isn't real, obviously. But congratulations on whatever epiphany you think you had. I tried to convince myself it meant something for a bit, but even if it's true, it means nothing. My life and my actions are still things I have to live with, and so are yours." She stares down at you. "I don't really care about the project. Not directly. I cared about John Leiblich."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "That makes one of us. What, you Jane's secret twin? That another one of your big bombshells that mean nothing? Can't imagine what business you'd have with that douche, aside from like-minds attracting one another."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "I thought he might know something. ...About her. About me. And about what's been happening more generally, I guess. But the man was impenetrable, and then he died. I figured it out, though. I should have noticed the key earlier. Obviously the thing that spawned you would also lie about his name." She smirks, and kicks you in the side.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Ow! Fuck off!" She stumbles to her feet "Voreverl Leocot *is* my... Ugh, who cares. I'll dispose of you after this, anyway. As I will with all of those who disrespect my authority. I'm not interested in the history of that foolish human waste, so it looks like we're done here."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "You should be proud. He was just as garbage as you, just as much of a coward. ...But he actually managed to kill his dad, so I guess you're still coming up short."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Voreverl Leocot does not have a father in any real sense. John Leiblich may have provided the seed for this body, but it is not even my original form. I simply stole his daughter's life away, that's all there is to it. He has no more relation to me than the factory workers who made my villainous attire."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "Not really. You can never escape what made you, raised you. I don't care about your sci-fi origin story, Jane. I never knew a fuckin' infant. That's not the girl I knew or the girl I hated. It's your family that ruined my life, you included. That ruined the life of an entire lineage. Isn't that funny? It is, isn't it? Maybe you should do that obnoxious cringeworthy laugh about it."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: She cocks her head to the side "It's... nice to know my presence has enough sheer potent evil energy to ruin your life, but... Uh, I mean... I can't find it funny if I don't know what you're talking about. Was there some scheme I forgot I played on you?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
"Of course you did. You took her from me. And then your father did. And none of that would ever have happened if it wasn't for everything else... if it wasn't for an absurd coincidence. The butterfly flapping its wings on the other side of the world. If your grandfather hadn't been a lunatic, a shitty one-dimensional fuckin' psychopath that set off events that would lead to a medical practitioner similarly losing his mind and abandoning his progeny to poverty." She picks up the box from earlier. "But I guess I should thank you. Now I know what I'm supposed to do. It shouldn't really be me here. But since it is, there's only really one ending."
She slides it in your direction with considerable effort. "Brought you a gift."

It topples over onto the ground still a reasonable distance from you, spilling its contents with a loud clattering. This thing is full of a somewhat obscene amount of close range combat weapons. There's daggers, a full on sword, a metal bat... almost anything you could think of. It's impressive this all could be acquired, and also how efficiently it was packed in there.

"I'm gonna kill you. Okay? Do your best to stop me."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl's eyes widen. She doesn't hesitate this time. No clever comebacks or stuttering surprise. She knows what she has to do.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: Voreverl Leocot makes a break for the stairs.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: Voreverl runs into the door, which is locked. This is confusing for multiple reasons.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "...Gweh... heh... good! Now you can't run away like a coward! Just... making sure we have a real cage match on our hands here!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Sure.” Her fists glint in the setting sunlight. “I still can’t bring myself to say her name. I don’t deserve it, Jane. See, I’m kind of a fucking monster. So seeing you play around like this… it’s a little irritating. Like appropriating someone’s culture.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "...That so? 'Cause I'm thinking it over, Vi, and you know what? You've got a pretty bona fide genuine heroic origin story on your hands. Revenge against the evil lineage that rules the land, oppressing your family. Yes... yes! You're so much better than that pirate, or that... girl, the blondie... whatever her face." She approaches the pile of weapons and searches for a shortsword "But guess what, champ? The hero *always* loses. Darth Vader cuts off Luke's hand and throws him down a pit! Thanos kills half of all life! Scar kills Mufasa! You've made your own funeral with all this dramatic finale talk!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
“Good.” She doesn’t dignify most of that with a response.

There’s a shortsword.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl brandishes her weapon of choice, one of the only ones she's at all familiar with using. "Better hope you're not overestimating your readiness for a fight to the death. Voreverl Leocot's heist is about to begin! The greatest one she's pulled since I took... Ah, yes, it was her hair ribbon, wasn't it? Alice's, that is. I'll steal your life like I stole your childhood friend's most valuable possession! What a fitting end! You should be grateful I put so much thought into your execution."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: She smiles. “Thanks, Jane.” Her expression darkens as she puts her fists up. “Maybe you’ll actually be able to amount to something.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl grits her teeth, tightens her grip, and begins her attack. She rushes Violetta with the sword, and attempts to plunge it into her.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: Violetta leaps out of the way. She haphazardly swipes at Voreverl, but it isn’t able to connect. “Just because I arranged this doesn’t mean I’m just gonna *give* it to you. Are you even trying?” She puts some distance between the two of you, which isn’t actually very smart since she needs an even closer range to be effective. “Hey, if you need motivation, killing me will mean you’ve committed two crimes total. That doubles your count. Big gain for evil, right? Pfahahaha!”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "You're the only one who needs motivation here! That's what makes heroes like you so weak! Evil rises out of nothing! You'll learn all about it once your world goes dark!" Voreverl rushes closer for another attempted impalement.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
“I just want you to shut the fuck up. It’s a stronger motive than you. I know you never gave a shit about me. Really appreciate you making the time anyway.”

Voreverl is now.  closer.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Never gave a shit about you? What did you expect? It's no fun to prank the school bully. You just would have... I mean, it's not like I'd be snuffing out any purity in the world, you know?" She stabs what she is aiming to be Violetta.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: She knocks the blade away with her fist. It’s unconventional, and does leave that hand bleeding even as she tried to center it on the brass knuckles. “Hrr… I wasn’t a bully, you fuck. I was a realist, and I only REALLY antagonized you, and I only did it because you deserve it. If you’re too much of a pansy to handle people hating you, maybe you should stop trying to make that happen, hm? But it’s fine. I’m used to being secondary in priority. Every fucking time.” She accentuates ‘fucking’ with a literal gut punch. using her other hand. It doesn’t draw blood, but it almost certainly bruises.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Gwgh... Hatred isn't my goal, just a side effect of fear. People fear what they don't understand, so I bet you're terrified of your place! Tell you what, let me make the pecking order clear here. You're not my first priority, true, but you're hardly my second. Even top ten would be a stretch! So, please, don't flatter yourself!" A third stab has hit Violetta's general direction.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
This connects. It penetrates her shirt and continues onward to create a sizable wound in her abdomen. It’s shallow, but the kind of thing that will cause serious problems if not treated. It knocks the air out of her, but she refocuses her vision quickly.

She uppercuts you in the jaw. “Maybe this’ll shut you up?” It miraculously doesn’t actually prevent you from speaking. It is, however, excruciating. She kicks you away, and with you, the blade.

“Second is… it’s a figure of speech, you fucking *(wheeze)* moron. I mean not first. I’m barely second for anyone either, yeah. You don’t have a list that goes that far, anyway. It’s just yourself at one, right?” She spits on the ground. “I never know what she saw in you. I-I only ever pitied you! Nothing else. But she… ohhh, she wouldn’t *ever*… Comes with being immature, I guess! It’s a sort of personality that appeals to a child. *(cough)* You’ve done a great job staying the exact! Fucking! Same! Right down to your first instinct being to run away, too! Hahaha!” She sidesteps around Voreverl. “…Only pitied at first, I guess. Obviously things have changed.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: With her skull throbbing, it becomes hard for Voreverl to focus on the words for a comeback. "Yeah... well... you..." Her eyes center on the hole punctured in Violetta "...should see a doctor... I mean, I'd send one of the zoo animals to the vet for that... Get better for our, uh, final battle... I can't demonstrate my full power on a crippled foe!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "...G...God, you're pathetic." That's all she has to say.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I don't... care! What you have to say." Voreverl aims the sword at Violetta "Insult me... fight me... it doesn't matter! Of course I stayed the same... I'm perfect! I'm evil! Voreverl Leocot cannot grow! I've already sunk as far as I can! So just... just die already... it'll act as a warning! It'll show everyone I mean business!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
“Haha… no. I won’t just bleed out. You won’t… you’re not going to get out of *this* one… just because everyone avoids you…” She stumbles forward, as if about to fall, and then transitions this into a roundhouse kick. It looks really cool, but doesn’t actually hurt like, at all. She misjudged the distance and it only grazed Voreverl. “No one will care. Just another runaway to file missing, another loose end for this stupid burro—bureaucratic conspiracy to sweep up. This does *nothing* for you. It’s a confrontation about me, for my sake only, and that’ll be my final revenge! You insufferable little *bitch*.”

She wipes her mouth. “You’ve had enough attention, anyway.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Revenge for what, you violent lunatic!? You heroes always pick the dumbest things to get upset over! You're in poverty because of... this body's father's father? And not even directly!? Go blame your own lineage for abandoning you, you idiot! Or is it *really* because Alice liked me more? Are you just jealous of how cool I am!? Come back and fight me when you actually care about striking down evil!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
"I'm not in poverty because of you. That's not what this is about. But I'm the... the only one who ever took you seriously. Even a little. You ruined that, of course. You ruin everything. I wanted to believe you so bad, Jane. But all you ever do is let me down. Even this." She gestures with her hands. 
"What the fuck is this?! This excuse for a fight. I *hate* you. I think you're a joke, you're pathetic, you can never amount to anything and I'll go until the day I dieeeee you bitch at long last why won't you fuckinggguuhhh--" She spits out blood.
"So strike me down, now. It can only be you. You know, I..." She laughs, holding her head. "When everything fell apart in succession, I tried to fill the void with love. I was a whooooore, Jane. Could've had some real nasty comeback material if you bothered to learn that, haha...! But none of those men ever loved me, or I them. It neeeever worked. I never thought of any of them when they weren't shoved directly into my face, they didn't-- like how babies, they don't have object permanend...nence. That was me with everyone. But not youuu... even after all these years, none of it has faded. You're the only person who's important to me, Jane. And I want you dead more than anything."
She looks down, her hair covering her face. "Funny."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "...Gweh...?" Voreverl drops her sword, not out of conscious thought, but because her hands automatically move to cover her own face. She can't confirm with a mirror, but she's pretty sure she feels herself blushing. "I'm... portant? I mean, of course I am! You can lie and... say you pity me, that I'm a joke, whatever! That's all just banter, isn't it!? My evil has consumed you! It's... you get it! You are my archnemesis, aren't you!? You recognize that killing me is more important than anything!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
Violetta looks back up quickly. She doesn't blush, maybe because her blood is occupied, but she's obviously incredibly caught off guard by this. "Y--archne-!? This isn't--you haven't consumed me! This is meaningless! It's not a victory, or a relationship, it's an ending, and that's the best you'll ever get. And I never--I never said I pitied... well, that was... back when we were, were..."
She grits her teeth. "Why can't you make anything easy?!"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Gweheheh..." Voreverl removes her hands for the sake of a full shrug "How could you have expected a duel with Voreverl Leocot, the bringer of darkness and all that is unholy, the baroness of the kingdom of evil, the embodiment of the plague of despair, to be easy!? You just sound like a glutton for punishment to me. You think one of us dying will end this... but our battle will be told for eons to come! It will become the foundation of all future legends passed down throughout mankind! You said it yourself! Nothing is more important than me and you, right here, right now!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: Violetta grabs your shoulders and shoves you against the rooftop door, taking advantage of your unarmed status. “How do you do it?! How do you so devotedly keep up the act of all this shit you must know is fucking nonsense?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "...How do *you* do it? How do you live your ordinary, simple, meaningless life? I can't pretend to be like you! Like anyone else! Like some caged animal, indistinguishable from any other lab rat running for the sake of some... incomprehensible societal goal! I don't care about the economy, about staying out of poverty, about your stupid petty little romances and families! How do you *not* want to be like me!? Like *Voreverl Leocot*!?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “It’s not a choice! It’s the truth. I *know* the truth. I’ve *seen* beyond the fucking veil, and it confirmed what I already knew. Dust in the wind!  All that we do is pointless. I can’t delude myself into believing there’s some grand meaning, or some ‘cool’ edgy aesthetic, to the things I want, the people I’ve hurt… oh, but you can. I’m soooo happy for you. You don’t get to live the miserable pathetic life you deserrrve. Because you *don’t care about society*… it must be nice to have that luxury. Haha!” She smiles exactly the way you’d expect someone livid and losing a lot of blood to. Her grip increases in pressure and trails closer to your neck.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "L-let go of me!" Voreverl grabs Violetta's arms and tries to pry them off of her "I'm not dying here! You're not dying here! Neither of us can, I won't let it happen! We've ascended beyond that! It will be legendary in scope! This is just the start of your harrowing journey to defeat me, to save humanity and achieve your vengeance, so let me go! Let me go!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
“Not this time, Jane.” She’s an incredibly strong woman. The physical resistance isn’t enough. Her grip around your throat tightens and makes it difficult to speak. “Ha. You’re begging. P…pathetic. I can’t believe you…”
She places the whole weight of her body against you. She falls forward, in other words. Her hands trail off you as her head limply makes contact with your torso, with the rest of her body stumbling to the ground. Violetta lays there, unconscious.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl immediately begins taking in gasps of air, making up for the flow lost only moments before. She holds a hand to her head and tries to construct a plan of action "Uh-uh... I need to... fuck, I need to, uh..." She reaches down for Violetta's wound, feeling around it "You're not supposed to remove the weapon... So... do I, like, put it back in now?" She angrily grabs and ruffles her hair, staining it with her blood soaked hands "Minions are supposed to take care of first aid!" Shoving Violetta aside, she rushes to the edge of the roof and scans for Dawn, or really any passersby.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
There doesn’t really seem to be anyone in the area. 

After a minute or so, DA opens the door to the rooftop, panting, PDA in hand. “You would not BELIEVE the shit I had to….” They notice the lifeless body. “Mm. Huh.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl whips around to face them, barking orders with a desperation in her voice "Help her! Do CPR! Or whatever! She... She's my new archenemy! I won't, uh... I can't grant her the pleasure of a quick death! Stop loafing around, minion, do something!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Fiiiiine.” DA removes their jacket which they’ve always had and fashions it into a compress for the wound, that kinda thing whatever the fuck you call it, then calls for an ambulance. “This place was supposed to be secret. Oh well.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Okay, let's book it! Obviously I can fight off the police, but... my energy's kinda drained right now. I'd have to, uh, show off some ultimate moves. Best to keep some secrets! You're a writer, you know what I mean. Save final forms for big reveals, and all that."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Ooh, irresponsible. Sure. I told ‘em she’s on the roof and everything’s unlocked now, so…” DA sighs, and heads back down the stairs.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl hurries after them, letting out occasional remarks of "Hurry!", "Come on, slowpoke!", and "Get a move on!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: The two clear the vicinity successfully. ((end session))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: DA slows down, catching their breath. "I think that's far enough..."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl matches their pace, but only once she's slightly ahead "Good... good. Yes. Anything, uh... on the PDA?" Voreverl scans the area to see if she's familiar with where they ended up.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "Some nonsense about intuition and a turtle. Nothing productive." They shrug and hand it to you.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl glances at the messages and pockets it. "Ugh... he should've intuited to buzz off. Wasting the time of the supreme lord of evil like that, unbelievable." She makes an attempt to wave down a cab.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: She does this.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: As in, a cab arrives.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Pretty climactic shit with you, it seems. Sad I missed it." DA.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Hardly. No hero worth their blessed salt would fall in their first real fight against the main villain. If she was ever in any danger, it wouldn't be worth calling a climax." She shoves DA into the cab and crawls in after them.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: They looks slightly annoyed by your pushing, but shrug it off. "You do know that's not exactly typical, right? People don't tend to get in that many fights. In real life, it's just one, and either they happen to never cross paths again or it ends with one of them dead. ...Of course, I prefer your approach, ideally. Lethality brings out character, so harnessing it without actual death is ideal. This is because dead people don't speak." DA explains.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Hey, cabbie, take us to Bioparco di Roma on the double. You'll face the wrath of a thousand plagues if you disobey or delay." author.name: natyobb

messages.content: "Yeah, because, you're supposed to represent me, right? In some like, nested insecurities way. Even though you're also not actually me. Because you're in my body, and you're an idiot." He sticks his hand on Furn's body, which he seems to be tangible to for some reason. "So the idea is like, I understand someone so important to me so little that I'd act like this? I guess? But it doesn't work, because like. I'm also here. I'm the one coming up with this. I understand that this is Furn's body with no life left in it. I can't gaslight my way out of that fact, you know?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "...What?" She stares at Furn "That... He's... Oh my God. He's just a machine though, right? He can be, like... I mean, there's plenty of vines... that could, uh, fuel..."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "No, it's about continuity of consciousness. You might be able to reuse the same vessel, but it wouldn't be Furn in any meaningful way." Bern rips out a part of Furn. It resembles a lighter. "I'd probably freak the fuck out in this situation, honestly. Definitely chilling and twisted to think about even with how baffling some of the rest of this is."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I guess that... makes sense. 'Cause we're... not the same either." Voreverl can feel her legs giving out, so she takes a seat on the vines. "The ship. It had to be that. He... he got damaged on impact... because I crashed it. And then he died here... I won. I killed your partner."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
“Nah, he’d win. Blunt impact isn’t the kind of thing that can take Furn down. I haven’t really thought about it, but it’d have to be something significantly more deliberate.”
Bern holds the lighter against one of the vines. 
“I’d like to wake up now.”
A fire rapidly starts spreading. 

Bern vanishes. I wonder if it will ever become clear what the fuck that was.
